(129, 9, 'Welcome to the Course', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"nice-to-meet-you-\">Nice to Meet You!</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/L--t1RtVD1s?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"Nd063-C2-L0-01-Instructor-Intro-Video\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"welcome-to-the-course-\">Welcome to the Course!</h2>\n<p>I’m Leslie, a Cloud Architect and Disaster Recovery Specialist from Chicago. Like some of you who are changing careers, I didn’t begin my career in IT. I’m actually a chemist who learned server technology on the job while working on a networked data system at a life sciences company. I\'ve been a cloud architect for about 5 years, and I’ve enjoyed every technology challenge and triumph along the way. </p>\n<p>I’m excited to be here sharing cloud technology lessons and guiding you through the beginning stages of what I’m sure will be exciting and rewarding careers in Cloud Architecture. </p>\n<p>The goal of this course is to provide you with the foundation you need to draw the necessary parallels between what we know as traditional on premises data center and the public cloud so that you can properly provision the resources in the cloud necessary for successful cloud deployments.</p>\n<h3 id=\"course-goal\">Course Goal</h3>\n<p>To the foundation you need to draw the necessary parallels between what we know as traditional on premises data center and the public cloud so that you can properly provision the resources in the cloud necessary for successful cloud deployments.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Let\'s get started!!!</em></strong></p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(130, 9, 'Course Structure', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JlVQnF3Eid4?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L0 07 This Course Has 4 Main Topics\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"what-we-will-learn-about-in-this-course\">What We Will Learn About in This Course</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Cost Optimization and Monitoring  </li>\n<li>Performance Optimization</li>\n<li>Serverless Technology</li>\n<li>Infrastructure as Code</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"course-structure\">Course Structure</h3>\n<p>The first half of the course covers broad topics that focus on how to make sure your environment is optimized for low cost and high performance.</p>\n<p>After that,  we\'ll get more technical, with a focus on AWS serverless technology, and how cost and performance optimization are built-in to the service platforms</p>\n<p>We will finish by introducing you to Terraform by Hashicorp, the platform agnostic tool for documenting your infrastructure as code.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Topics We Will Cover: Costs and Monitoring, Cloud Performance, IaC, Serverless Computing\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/March/5e6a7dcc_cand-l0-what-cover/cand-l0-what-cover.jpg\" width=\"960px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Topics We Will Cover </p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 2</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What is the url for the AWS console website?<br/> <strong><em>Hint:</em></strong> <em>if you aren\'t sure, try the links and see where they take you</em></p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-10\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-10\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-10\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-10\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon.com</a></p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p><a href=\"https://console.aws.amazon.com\" target=\"_blank\">console.aws.amazon.com</a></p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-11\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-11\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-11\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-11\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p><a href=\"https://awsconsole.com\" target=\"_blank\">awsconsole.com</a></p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-12\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk4-12\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk4-12\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-12\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p><a href=\"https://amazon.aws.com\" target=\"_blank\">amazon.aws.com</a></p>\n</div></label></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"radio-quiz-atom--buttons--Y7OWz _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--container--mpad_\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--reflect-header--38-vS\"><h2>Thinking Like a Cloud Architect</h2><div class=\"open-response-atom--answered-icon--_GQ1N\"></div></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What topic are you most looking forward to exploring during this course?</p>\n</div><span><div><hr/><div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Your reflection</h3></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-answer-container--2c9-l\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--answer--1QIQc\"><strong class=\"light\">The most thing I am caring about is How low cost and high performance aws infrastructures are built.</strong></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-button-container--8XM8j\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--default vds-button__icon vds-button__icon--left\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\"><i aria-hidden=\"false\" aria-label=\"Edit Answer\" class=\"vds-icon\" role=\"img\"><svg viewbox=\"0 0 32 32\"><path d=\"M15 6a1 1 0 01.117 1.993L15 8h-5a2 2 0 00-1.995 1.85L8 10v12a2 2 0 001.85 1.995L10 24h12a2 2 0 001.995-1.85L24 22v-3l.007-.117a1 1 0 01.876-.876L25 18a1 1 0 01.993.883L26 19v3a4 4 0 01-3.8 3.995L22 26H10a4 4 0 01-3.995-3.8L6 22V10a4 4 0 013.8-3.995L10 6h5zm9.669-.294l.11.102 1.413 1.414a2 2 0 01.102 2.719l-.102.11-1.414 1.413a1.99 1.99 0 01-.896.518 1.98 1.98 0 01-.396.763l-.122.134-7.354 7.354a2 2 0 01-.782.483l-.18.05-1.836.427a2 2 0 01-2.432-2.236l.03-.16.422-1.84a2 2 0 01.41-.829l.125-.138 7.354-7.354a1.99 1.99 0 01.898-.518c.072-.273.204-.535.395-.763l.122-.133 1.414-1.414a2 2 0 012.719-.102zm-4.133 4.344l-7.354 7.354-.422 1.84 1.836-.426 7.354-7.354-1.414-1.414zm2.828-2.828L21.95 8.636l1.414 1.414 1.414-1.414-1.414-1.414z\"></path></svg></i></span></button></div></div></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Things to think about</h3></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>I am truly passionate about cloud technology, so it is hard to pick one topic that interests me the most. I am going to go with Infrastructure as Code. It is an exciting and innovative concept that coincides with another passion of mine: Disaster Recovery. I have never had the opportunity to recover a production environment from a configuration file, but I’d like to see the technology in action someday-  during a disaster recovery test and not an actual disaster!</p>\n</div></div></span></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>');
INSERT INTO `chapitre` (`id_chapitre`, `id_lesson`, `nom_chapitre`, `HTML`) VALUES
(131, 9, 'Performance Efficiency in the Cloud', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/kGhKRwij1gk?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L0 02 Traditional Vs Cloud\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"four-cloud-models\">Four Cloud Models</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Private Cloud</strong>:  Organization  owns, operates, and governs their cloud computing resources.  </p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Community Cloud</strong>: Cloud resources provided for organizations and community groups.  </p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Public Cloud</strong>: Owned by the government, academic institutions, or a business (e.g. Amazon Web Services, Microsoft Azure and Google Cloud Platform).  </li>\n<li><strong>Hybrid Cloud</strong>:  Combines public cloud and private cloud to allow data and resources to be shared between them.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Four cloud models- private, community, public, and hybrid\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/March/5e6a7df6_cand-c2-l0-four-models/cand-c2-l0-four-models.jpg\" width=\"728px\"/></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Quiz Question</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Which Cloud Models involve providers like Amazon Web Services and Microsoft Azure?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk1-7\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-7\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-7\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk1-7\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Private Cloud</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Public Cloud</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-8\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-8\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-8\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Community Cloud</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Hybrid Cloud</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"new-terms-br-br-\">New Terms<br/><br/></h3>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:left\">Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Cloud</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Servers and resources that are accessed over the internet</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>On-premises</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Hardware and software that is contained within the physical confines of a business or their assigned section of a data center</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(132, 9, 'Getting to Faster and Cheaper', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/lHZoMc3KYWk?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L0 03 General Efficiencies For Instances, Databases Storage, And Network\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Moving to the cloud doesn’t guarantee that your application will be faster and cost less to operate</strong>. In fact, without the proper baseline metrics, you won’t know where to start when planning your move.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Most performance issues can be traced to the application itself</strong> and some applications will need to be redesigned to be cloud native in order to achieve truly optimized performance.  Common causes of performance issues:   </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Poorly designed applications  </li>\n<li>Database design constraints  </li>\n<li>Inefficient network routes  </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Moving to the cloud should improve network response times.</strong>  Global edge cache locations can bring the server closer to the end user.    </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--container--mpad_\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--reflect-header--38-vS\"><h2>Free Response Quiz</h2></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What do you think is the best service cloud providers offer their customers?</p>\n</div><span><div><textarea class=\"open-response-atom--textarea--2YCpW\" placeholder=\"Enter your response here, there\'s no right or wrong answer\"></textarea><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" disabled=\"\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></span></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 2</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>How do edge locations deliver content to users faster?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By moving it closer</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk2-10\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-10\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-10\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk2-10\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By breaking it into smaller files</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-11\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-11\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-11\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-11\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By decreasing the resolution</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-12\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk4-12\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk4-12\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-12\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By using satellites</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"radio-quiz-atom--buttons--Y7OWz _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"high-performance-in-the-cloud-vs-high-performance-computing\">High Performance In the Cloud vs. High Performance Computing</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2g7D4zqvryc?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 L0 04 High Performance Computing\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Supercomputing harnesses the computing power of multiple computers and aggregates them to tackle complex problems in business and academia.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>In supercomputing, computers are called nodes and nodes are organized into groups called clusters.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Supercomputing is the ultimate in high performance computing in the cloud.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"new-terms-br-br-\">New Terms<br/><br/></h3>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:left\">Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Baseline</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Measurement of conditions at the start of your project used to make planning decisions</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cloud Computing</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Storing and accessing data and applications over the Internet instead of a local or networked computer\'s hard drive</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>High Performance Computing (a.k.a. supercomputing)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Supercomputing harnesses the computing power of multiple computers and aggregates them to tackle complex problems in business and academia</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Infrastructure as Code</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">The process of provisioning and managing your cloud resources by writing a template file that is both human-readable, and machine-consumable</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Serverless</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Compute model where the developer doesn’t need to be concerned with the server because the cloud provider takes care of it</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"additional-reading\">Additional Reading</h2>\n<p>Please follow the links below to learn more about Amazon’s managed database services, their on premises hybrid cloud offering, and high performance computing in the AWS cloud.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/rds/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS RDS</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.zdnet.com/article/aws-outpost-brings-its-cloud-hardware-on-premises/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Outposts Brings AWS Cloud Hardware on Premises</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/hpc/\" target=\"_blank\">HPC on AWS</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(133, 9, 'Defining Goals', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/uvZhdrqiO7A?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L0 05 Define The Goals And Measure Them\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Planning to move to the cloud is a process that requires pragmatism and neutrality to make the best decisions for your technology.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>The team is comprised of directors, managers, and engineers from Infrastructure, Operations, and Software Engineering teams</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>It is important to define your migrations goals and base your migration plans on your actual metrics. Metrics provide the information you need to make data-driven decisions. </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"examples-of-cloud-migration-goals-\">Examples Of Cloud Migration Goals:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>We are migrating to the cloud to reduce our infrastructure costs by 25%</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>We believe that by hosting our application in AWS, we will be able to deliver download speeds that are 60% faster than our baseline</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>We are going to duplicate our infrastructure in the cloud and maintain our AWS account as a warm backup site for disaster recovery</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>We are consolidating our data centers and moving to the cloud because our AWS account will provide one centralized view into our environment with more visibility into how our compute spend is being utilized.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"additional-reading\">Additional Reading</h2>\n<p>The links below offer additional insight into the practice of cloud migration, and will offer you further details into the scope, procedures, and goals of a cloud migration project.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cloudindustryforum.org/content/getting-cloud-faster-5-ws-cloud-migration\" target=\"_blank\">The 5 “W\'s of Cloud Migration</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/cloud-migration/\" target=\"_blank\">Cloud Migration</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(134, 9, 'Historical Context', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"historical-context-for-performance-in-the-cloud\">Historical Context for Performance in the Cloud</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/41yZ6iKTvcM?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L0 06 Historical Context\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>AWS was started to sell excess compute capacity owned by Amazon\'s e-commerce business.  The on-demand, no-contract service model has revolutionized IT operations.</li>\n<li>Managing cloud spend is a significant challenge for many organizations. </li>\n<li>Cloud architects who understand how to manage both performance and cost are in high demand.</li>\n<li>Our primary focus will be on technology provided by AWS, but the underlying concepts we discuss apply to all cloud providers. </li>\n<li>In this course, \"Amazon\" refers to AWS (Amazon Web Services), the cloud platform segment of Amazon Inc., which also owns the e-commerce giant Amazon.com. </li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"aws-changes-frequently-\">AWS Changes Frequently!</h4>\n<p>What you see in the course may not match what you see when you access AWS yourself. This course reflects how the AWS management console looks and functions in March of 2020.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS documentation</a> is a great place to find the latest information.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(135, 9, 'Getting Started: AWS Console', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"the-aws-console\">The AWS Console</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/50ArQoNWrxY?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L0 08 AWS Services In The Console\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<p>AWS now has over 175 branded services available via the console. While it is great to familiarize yourself with their names and functionality, it isn’t realistic to expect to learn how to use all of them during this program.</p>\n<p>New services are added and existing services are updated regularly. You\'ll want to follow the AWS blogs, watch their broadcasts on YouTube, and read their documentation and FAQs for details on new and updated services.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"additional-reading\">Additional Reading</h2>\n<p>As you progress in your careers, you will become familiar with AWS notices and bulletins about new cloud services and you’ll hear the voices of experts in cloud technology. It is always advisable to stay updated on the latest updates by subscribing to AWS newsletters, listening to podcasts, and reading blog posts by cloud experts.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS News Blog</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/new/?whats-new-content-all.sort-by=item.additionalFields.postDateTime&amp;whats-new-content-all.sort-order=desc&amp;wn-featured-announcements.sort-by=item.additionalFields.numericSort&amp;wn-featured-announcements.sort-order=asc\" target=\"_blank\">What’s New With AWS</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/releasenotes/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Release Notes</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://awsinsider.net/Home.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Insider</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/aws/\" target=\"_blank\">Reddit | Amazon Web Services</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(136, 9, 'Prerequisites and Tools Needed', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"tools-needed-for-this-course\">Tools Needed for This Course</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"are-you-ready-to-begin-the-course-\">Are You Ready to Begin the Course?</h2>\n<h3 id=\"prerequisites\">Prerequisites</h3>\n<p>Prior experience as a Cloud architect is not required, but you should have experience with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Using the Command Line Interface</li>\n<li>Basic scripting</li>\n<li>Familiarity with Web application architecture, hosting, infrastructure, and components</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"tools-needed\">Tools Needed</h3>\n<p>To successfully complete this course you will need:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>AWS CLI and Terraform installed on your local machine </li>\n<li>An integrated development environment (IDE) like VS Code or Atom</li>\n<li>Acces to diagramming application like Lucid Chart or Diagrams.net</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"installation-instructions\">Installation Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-chap-install.html\" target=\"_blank\">AWS CLI Installation Instructions</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://learn.hashicorp.com/terraform/getting-started/install.html\" target=\"_blank\">Terraform Installation Instructions</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"suggested-ides\">Suggested IDEs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\" target=\"_blank\">VS Code</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://atom.io/\" target=\"_blank\">Atom</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.sublimetext.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sublime Text</a> </li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"suggested-diagramming-applications\">Suggested Diagramming Applications</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.lucidchart.com/\" target=\"_blank\">LucidChart</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://creately.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Creatly</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.diagrams.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Diagrams.net</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gliffy.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Gliffy</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>You\'ll also need access to the AWS Console. See the next page for instructions.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"task-list-atom--container--WBrU5\"><header class=\"task-list-atom--header--3bRGC\"><h3 class=\"task-list-atom--title--1bHiw\">Get Ready for the Course!</h3><h5 class=\"task-list-atom--description--1K-fr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Please complete all of the items in the checklist:</p>\n</div></h5></header><div class=\"task-list-atom--tasks-container--3MvCe\"><span class=\"task-list-atom--icon-container--3-v6v\">Task List</span><ul class=\"task-list-atom--tasks-checkbox-container--LMF6d\"><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824764--0\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824764--0\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824764--0\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824764--0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Install the AWS CLI</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824764--1\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824764--1\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824764--1\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824764--1\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Install and configure your preferred IDE to your liking</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824764--2\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824764--2\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824764--2\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824764--2\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Install Terraform</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824764--3\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824764--3\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824764--3\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824764--3\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Identify a diagramming application for creating architectural diagrams</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li></ul></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(137, 9, 'Course - AWS Sign In and Costs', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"launch-the-aws-web-console-from-your-udacity-classroom\">Launch the AWS Web Console from your Udacity Classroom</h2>\n<p>You are given a <em>federated user account</em>, a temporary AWS user account with limited permissions, that you can use in this program. </p>\n<p>Before you begin, be sure to <strong>log out</strong> of any AWS instances you may already have running. Then click on the <strong>“LAUNCH CLOUD GATEWAY” </strong>link in the left navigation pane to access a customized instance with the right permissions specific to this program. It will open up a pop-up, and clicking on the <strong>\"Open AWS Console\"</strong> button in the pop-up will open the AWS console in a new browser tab. This may take a few moments to load the first time. See a brief video below for a walkthrough.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><blockquote>\n<p>Ensure that you do not have a pop-up blocker installed; it may prevent the new tab from launching.  Please be sure to allow pop-ups from Udacity. </p>\n</blockquote>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Animation of launching the AWS console explained above\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/August/611db29c_aws-console-re-edit-1/aws-console-re-edit-1.gif\" width=\"1920px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Animation of launching the AWS console</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"important-points-to-remember\">Important Points to Remember</h3>\n<h4 id=\"1-session-limit\"><strong>1. Session limit</strong></h4>\n<p><span>Note that there is a certain <strong>session time limit</strong>. If reached, you will automatically be timed out. As long as you have not used your entire allocated budget, your work will be saved.  You can re-launch using the same \"Launch Cloud Gateway\" button in the left navigation menu to return to your session. </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"2-default-aws-region\"><strong>2. Default AWS region</strong></h4>\n<p>The default AWS region for you will be US East (N. Virginia) (<em>us-east-1</em>). \nHowever, you can switch and practice in <code>us-west-2</code> region as well. Note: You might not have necessary permissions to complete this course if you select regions other than <code>us-east-1</code> and <code>us-west-2</code>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"3-the-budget-allocated-for-you\"><strong>3. The budget allocated for you</strong></h4>\n<p>All AWS services are a pay-as-you-go service. Udacity has set a budget for each student to complete their course work.  Please understand that these credits are limited and available for you to use judiciously. <b> <font color=\"red\">The budget for this entire course is $25. </font></b> Although, we find about $10 sufficient for most to complete this course. </p>\n<h4 id=\"-b-4-font-color-red-shut-down-your-resources-no-extra-credits-font-b-\"><b>4. <font color=\"red\"> Shut down your resources | No extra credits </font></b></h4>\n<p>We recommend you <strong>shut down/delete every AWS resource</strong> (e.g., EC2, Sagemaker, Database, EMR, CloudFormation) immediately after the usage or if you are stepping away for a few hours. Otherwise, you will run out of your allocated budget.\n<b><font color=\"red\"> Udacity will not provide additional credits.</font></b> In case you exhaust your credits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>You will lose your progress on the AWS console.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>You will have to use your personal AWS account to finish the remaining ND.</strong>\nEven if you are in the middle of the project/exercise and need to step away, you must shut down your resources. You can re-instantiate them later. To better understand pricing, see the <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Pricing</a> for all available services. &gt; For reference, any service available to you @$0.1/hour or higher should be monitored closely and shut down immediately after use or if you are stepping away.  &gt;</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Check the pricing at https://aws.amazon.com/pricing/\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/April/60828d1d_screenshot-2021-04-16-at-2.55.57-pm/screenshot-2021-04-16-at-2.55.57-pm.png\" width=\"500px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Check the pricing at <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">https://aws.amazon.com/pricing/</a></p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h4 id=\"5-tracking-your-usage\"><strong>5. Tracking your usage</strong></h4>\n<p>You need to make sure that you have an adequate budget available to complete your project/task. <b><font color=\"red\">If you hit your budget, your session will time out and your work will be lost and unrecoverable. </font></b>  Options for you to stay vigilant are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Track your usage on the AWS web console. Go to <a href=\"https://console.aws.amazon.com/billing/home#/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Billing Dashboard</a>, and view the monthly spending. It will list you the services constituting the spend. <br/></li>\n<li>Submit a <a href=\"https://udacity.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new?ticket_form_id=110806\" target=\"_blank\">ticket</a> to Student Support Services to know your current balance.<br/></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"AWS Billing dashboard\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/April/60828964_screenshot-2021-04-23-at-2.02.34-pm/screenshot-2021-04-23-at-2.02.34-pm.png\" width=\"600px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Billing dashboard</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong> -<br/>As you are given a temporary AWS user account with <strong>limited</strong> permissions, you might not be able to avail <strong>all</strong> AWS services. We have allowed the necessary ones only. If you see a few warning messages related to insufficient permissions, you can ignore them and proceed with your practice.  </p>\n</blockquote>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 2</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select all of the true statements about AWS usage.</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Any service at $0.1/hour or higher should be monitored closely and shut down immediately after use to avoid exhausting your budget </p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--a1619168634849-16\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--a1619168634849-16\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--a1619168634849-16\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--a1619168634849-16\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>All progress on the AWS console will be saved even if you exhaust your budget </p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Most students have completed the program using about $10 from their budget </p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>You will have to work with your personal AWS account to finish the program if you exhaust your budget </p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>You can track your monthly usage of credits within the AWS billing dashboard </p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--5c1fa03e-611f-45a2-8f65-1e62f7ae6d53-17\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--5c1fa03e-611f-45a2-8f65-1e62f7ae6d53-17\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--5c1fa03e-611f-45a2-8f65-1e62f7ae6d53-17\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--5c1fa03e-611f-45a2-8f65-1e62f7ae6d53-17\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>You may use an existing personal or federated AWS account for this program.</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 2</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What is the default AWS region set to?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--a1619169346800-18\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--a1619169346800-18\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--a1619169346800-18\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--a1619169346800-18\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>US East (Ohio) (us-east-2) </p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>US East (N. Virginia) (us-east-1) </p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--a1619169394849-19\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--a1619169394849-19\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--a1619169394849-19\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--a1619169394849-19\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>US West (N. California) (us-west-1)</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--a1619169402489-20\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--a1619169402489-20\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--a1619169402489-20\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--a1619169402489-20\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>US West (Oregon) (us-west-2)</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"radio-quiz-atom--buttons--Y7OWz _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>');
INSERT INTO `chapitre` (`id_chapitre`, `id_lesson`, `nom_chapitre`, `HTML`) VALUES
(138, 9, '[Optional] Connect VS Code to AWS', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"connect-the-vs-code-to-aws-account\">Connect the VS Code to AWS Account</h2>\n<p>There is a plug-in, <strong>AWS Toolkit</strong>, available for the Visual Studio Code using which you can create/configure/delete any AWS resource. </p>\n<h3 id=\"1-install-aws-toolkit-in-vs-code\">1. Install AWS Toolkit in VS Code</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Start your VS code editor, and switch to the <strong>Extensions</strong> tab.</li>\n<li>Search and install the <strong>AWS Toolkit</strong> plug-in, as shown in the snapshot below.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Install AWS Toolkit Extension\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/May/60a1f807_aws-toolkit-installation/aws-toolkit-installation.png\" width=\"500px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Install AWS Toolkit Extension</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ul>\n<li>Once the plug-in is installed, you will see the AWS icon in the tool bar, and a starter tutorial on how to connect to AWS. We have explained the steps below as well.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Successfully installed AWS Toolkit and a starter tutorial on how to connect to AWS\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/August/611f8915_screenshot-2021-08-20-at-4.19.02-pm/screenshot-2021-08-20-at-4.19.02-pm.png\" width=\"700px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Successfully installed AWS Toolkit and a starter tutorial on how to connect to AWS</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"2-provide-access-key\">2. Provide Access Key</h3>\n<p>The steps below will create <code>config</code> and <code>credentials</code> files automatically, that will store the AWS credentials (Access Key) and some default configurations (such as region). </p>\n<ol>\n<li><p>Open the <strong>Command Palette</strong> in the VS Code editor. To do so, either choose on the Menu bar ? View ? Command Palette or use the following shortcut keys:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Windows and Linux: <strong>Ctrl+Shift+P</strong></li>\n<li>macOS: <strong>Command+Shift+P</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><p>Search for AWS and choose <strong>AWS: Create Credentials Profile</strong>. Note that this option can also be used for updating the existing profile. If you already have any profile set already, then the <code>config</code> and <code>credentials</code> files will open up for editing, as shown below. </p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"The `config` and `credentials` files opened up for editing\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/September/61419dc0_screenshot-2021-09-15-at-12.40.38-pm/screenshot-2021-09-15-at-12.40.38-pm.png\" width=\"700px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>The <code>config</code> and <code>credentials</code> files opened up for editing. Notice the <code>[default]</code> profile only. </p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"3\">\n<li><p>Provide a profile name of your choice or choose <code>default</code>, along with <strong>access key ID, secret access key</strong>, and the <strong>session token</strong>, as highlighted in the snapshot above. </p>\n<p>You can copy the value of access key ID, secret access key, and the session token from the pop up that come after clicking on the <strong>\"OPEN AWS GATEWAY\"</strong> link in the left navigation pane of the classroom. You will have to copy-paste the following values:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-bash\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\"># credentials file showing a Default profile</span>\n[default]\naws_access_key_id=*****\naws_secret_access_key=*******\naws_session_token=***********************\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\"># config file</span>\n[default]\nregion = us-east-<span class=\"hljs-number\">1</span>\noutput = json\n</code></pre>\n<p>Note that a profile is analogous to a single AWS account. If you have multiple AWS accounts, you can create mutiple profiles locally.  </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><font color=\"RED\"><strong>Note</strong></font> Classroom generated access key ID, secret access key, and the session token are valid only for the current session duration - 4 hours. <strong>You will have to refresh the classroom page, regenerate the Access Key again, and save them again in the VScode.</strong> </p>\n</blockquote>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\'Access key that pops up after clicking on the **\"OPEN AWS GATEWAY\"** link in the left navigation pane.\' class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/June/60d44c55_launch-aws-gateway/launch-aws-gateway.png\" width=\"500px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Access key that pops up after clicking on the <strong>\"OPEN AWS GATEWAY\"</strong> link in the left navigation pane.</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"4\">\n<li>Later in this program, if you generate <strong>permanent</strong> Access key (id and secret) using AWS IAM service, you can save them in the VSCode the same way explained above, and delete the <code>aws_session_token</code>, as shown in the snapshot below. Otherwise, you may encounter <code>InvalidClientTokenId</code> error while running AWS CLI commands. </li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Delete the `aws_session_token` when you are using the **permanent** Access key\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/November/618b7abc_screenshot-2021-11-10-at-1.21.42-pm/screenshot-2021-11-10-at-1.21.42-pm.png\" width=\"700px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Delete the <code>aws_session_token</code> when you are using the <strong>permanent</strong> Access key</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"3-connect-to-aws\">3. Connect to AWS</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Open the <strong>Command Palette</strong> in the VS Code editor.</li>\n<li>Search for AWS and choose <strong>AWS: Connect to AWS</strong></li>\n<li>Choose a profile you have created in the step above.  </li>\n<li>On a successful connection, <strong>AWS: profile:XXXXXX</strong> will appear at the bottom left of VS Code window.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Choosing **AWS: Connect to AWS** option \" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/May/60a20143_nd063-c3-design-for-security-project-starter-2021-05-17-11-08-08/nd063-c3-design-for-security-project-starter-2021-05-17-11-08-08.png\" width=\"600px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Choosing <strong>AWS: Connect to AWS</strong> option </p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Successful AWS Connection Indicator\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/May/60a201d6_nd063-c3-design-for-security-project-starter-2021-05-17-11-10-15/nd063-c3-design-for-security-project-starter-2021-05-17-11-10-15.png\" width=\"500px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Successful AWS Connection Indicator</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(139, 9, 'Recap', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/zm5Rae0LMyA?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L0 09 Intro Outro\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"are-you-ready-\">Are You Ready?</h2>\n<p>Now that you are familiar and with the concepts we will be covering in this course, please take the time to make sure you are prepared by reviewing the requirements checklist below.</p>\n<h2 id=\"approaching-the-course\">Approaching the Course</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Give yourself the space to absorb it all</li>\n<li>Allow yourself the freedom to imagine all of the possibilities cloud computing provides</li>\n<li>Think about how cloud might resolve a technology obstacle you’ve been </li>\n<li>Give yourself time to integrate and comprehend the lessons. </li>\n<li>Read the articles and watch the videos at the end of the modules for greater depth of understanding. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Mastery of the cloud is much closer than you think!</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"task-list-atom--container--WBrU5\"><header class=\"task-list-atom--header--3bRGC\"><h3 class=\"task-list-atom--title--1bHiw\">Course Requirements Checklist</h3><h5 class=\"task-list-atom--description--1K-fr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>You\'ll be ready to start the course when you have completed all of these items:</p>\n</div></h5></header><div class=\"task-list-atom--tasks-container--3MvCe\"><span class=\"task-list-atom--icon-container--3-v6v\">Task List</span><ul class=\"task-list-atom--tasks-checkbox-container--LMF6d\"><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--0\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824925--0\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824925--0\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Sign In to the AWS Console</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--1\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824925--1\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824925--1\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--1\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Install and configure your preferred IDE to your liking</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--2\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824925--2\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824925--2\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--2\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Install the AWS CLI</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--3\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824925--3\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824925--3\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--3\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Identify a diagramming application for creating architectural diagrams</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--4\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824925--4\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824925--4\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824925--4\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Install Terraform</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li></ul></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(140, 9, 'Glossary', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"new-terms-in-this-lesson\">New Terms in This Lesson</h2>\n<p><br/>\n<br/> </p>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:left\">Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Baseline</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Measurement of conditions at the start of your project used to make planning decisions</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cloud</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Servers and resources that are accessed over the internet</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cloud Computing</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Storing and accessing data and applications over the Internet instead of a local or networked computer\'s hard drive</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>High Performance Computing (a.k.a. supercomputing)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Supercomputing harnesses the computing power of multiple computers and aggregates them to tackle complex problems in business and academia</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Infrastructure as Code</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">The process of provisioning and managing your cloud resources by writing a template file that is both human readable, and machine consumable</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>On-premises</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Hardware and software that is contained within the physical confines of a business or their assigned section of a data center</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Serverless</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Compute model where the developer doesn’t need to be concerned with the server because the cloud provider takes care of it</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(141, 10, 'Lesson Intro', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-wOzIJ-ZTKk?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 01 Lesson Intro\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<p>Managing cloud spend is one of the major challenges facing experienced IT organizations today.   </p>\n<p>In this lesson, we will cover:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cloud Costs  </li>\n<li>Service Pricing</li>\n<li>Cost Management</li>\n<li>Cost Optimization and Monitoring    </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"This lesson is about Costs and Monitoring\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8bddca_cand-l1-costs-and-monitoring/cand-l1-costs-and-monitoring.jpg\" width=\"684px\"/></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(142, 10, 'Intro to Costs in the Cloud', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"how-the-aws-cost-structure-works\">How the AWS Cost Structure Works</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/DLmtjxo1iVY?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 02 How AWS Cost Structure Works\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>To harness the full power of public cloud computing, you need to have a firm grasp of costs, strategy, and trade-offs. </p>\n<p>Cloud costs are based on usage. AWS offers as much compute on-demand as you want and are willing to pay for. However, their on-demand pricing is the most expensive option.  You can realize major savings by planning out a cloud strategy and taking advantage of the optimization options we will learn about in the following sections</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 4</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What is the public cloud (choose two)</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>A virtual data center accessible to anyone over the internet</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-13\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-13\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-13\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-13\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>A virtual data center owned and operated by a publicly-traded company</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-14\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-14\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-14\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-14\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Amazon.com</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>A style of computing where anyone can use services with no guarantee where the data will be stored</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 4</h3><div class=\"index-module--markdown--2MdcR ureact-markdown\"><p>Please match the infrastructure and service costs with their associated infrastructure environment</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-choices--2ziSF\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Answer choice selections - tab through answer choices to match to concepts below.\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><h3>Submit to check your answer choices!</h3></div></div><div class=\"index--labels--tWrVZ\"><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Infrastructure Services and Costs</p>\n</div></h3><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p> Infrastructure Environment</p>\n</div></h3></div><div class=\"index--answer-selections--3mNdz\"><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Data Transfer</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Data Transfer - currently AWS\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>OS Licenses</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"OS Licenses - currently Data Center\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, Data Center.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Data Center</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Hardware Leases</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Hardware Leases - currently Data Center\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, Data Center.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Data Center</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Compute by the Second</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"\nCompute by the Second - currently AWS\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Unused Storage</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"\nUnused Storage - currently Data Center\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, Data Center.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Data Center</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Email Support</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Email Support - currently AWS\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--buttons--2-6jY _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"aws-cost-calculators\">AWS Cost Calculators</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/z6p1A6VfxT0?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 03 Cost Calculators\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"three-ways-to-calculate-aws-costs\">Three Ways to Calculate AWS Costs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Simple Monthly Calculator</strong> - allows you to explore AWS services, model solutions, and create estimates for the cost of your use cases on AWS  </li>\n<li><strong>TCO Calculator</strong> - used to compare the cost of running your applications in an on-premises or colocation environment to AWS  </li>\n<li><strong>AWS Pricing Calculator</strong> (NEW- replaces the Simple Monthly Calculator)  </li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"use-the-aws-free-tier-wisely\">Use the   AWS Free Tier Wisely</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Not all services are included the Free Tier and Free Tier services have limits  </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>See the details\nin the <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/free/free-tier-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\">Free Tier FAQs</a></p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Track your Free Tier usage here:  <a href=\"https://console.aws.amazon.com/billing/home#/freetier\" target=\"_blank\">All Free Tier services by usage</a> </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"secure-your-aws-account-with-2-factor-authentication\">Secure your AWS Account with 2-Factor Authentication</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>it is your responsibility to secure your account and prevent unauthorized use.</li>\n<li>If  you haven’t already configured your AWS account for 2-factor authentication, do it now: <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/id_credentials_mfa_enable_virtual.html\" target=\"_blank\">Enable MFA</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 3 of 4</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Which of these options is a paid AWS service?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk1-15\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-15\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-15\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk1-15\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Uploading files to S3</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-16\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-16\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-16\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-16\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Creating an EC2 instance</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Storing multimedia files in S3</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Maintaining an unused 2TB RDS database snapshot</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Developer Support</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--container--mpad_\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--reflect-header--38-vS\"><h2>Think Like a Cloud Architect</h2><div class=\"open-response-atom--answered-icon--_GQ1N\"></div></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Why is it important to enable two-factor authentication on your AWS account? </p>\n</div><span><div><hr/><div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Your reflection</h3></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-answer-container--2c9-l\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--answer--1QIQc\"><strong class=\"light\">For more security and to prevent malicious usage of your account.</strong></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-button-container--8XM8j\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--default vds-button__icon vds-button__icon--left\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\"><i aria-hidden=\"false\" aria-label=\"Edit Answer\" class=\"vds-icon\" role=\"img\"><svg viewbox=\"0 0 32 32\"><path d=\"M15 6a1 1 0 01.117 1.993L15 8h-5a2 2 0 00-1.995 1.85L8 10v12a2 2 0 001.85 1.995L10 24h12a2 2 0 001.995-1.85L24 22v-3l.007-.117a1 1 0 01.876-.876L25 18a1 1 0 01.993.883L26 19v3a4 4 0 01-3.8 3.995L22 26H10a4 4 0 01-3.995-3.8L6 22V10a4 4 0 013.8-3.995L10 6h5zm9.669-.294l.11.102 1.413 1.414a2 2 0 01.102 2.719l-.102.11-1.414 1.413a1.99 1.99 0 01-.896.518 1.98 1.98 0 01-.396.763l-.122.134-7.354 7.354a2 2 0 01-.782.483l-.18.05-1.836.427a2 2 0 01-2.432-2.236l.03-.16.422-1.84a2 2 0 01.41-.829l.125-.138 7.354-7.354a1.99 1.99 0 01.898-.518c.072-.273.204-.535.395-.763l.122-.133 1.414-1.414a2 2 0 012.719-.102zm-4.133 4.344l-7.354 7.354-.422 1.84 1.836-.426 7.354-7.354-1.414-1.414zm2.828-2.828L21.95 8.636l1.414 1.414 1.414-1.414-1.414-1.414z\"></path></svg></i></span></button></div></div></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Things to think about</h3></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Thanks for your response. Using two-factor authentication reduces the risk of someone gaining unauthorized access to your AWS account by adding one additional step to authenticate your identity.</p>\n</div></div></span></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"links-to-resources-to-learn-more-about-data-center-vs-cloud-costs\">Links to resources to learn more about Data Center vs Cloud Costs</h3>\n<p>To learn more about how AWS prices its services, how modern teams view cloud compute, and how to avoid unexpected and unwelcome charges on your monthly AWS bill, please read the articles and posts at the links below</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@Joachim8675309/devops-concepts-pets-vs-cattle-2380b5aab313\" target=\"_blank\">Pets vs. Cattle</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeline_of_Amazon_Web_Services\" target=\"_blank\">Timeline of Amazon Web Services</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/pricing-calculator/latest/userguide/what-is-pricing-calculator.html\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Pricing Calculator</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/awsaccountbilling/latest/aboutv2/checklistforunwantedcharges.html\" target=\"_blank\">Avoiding Unexpected Charges</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>');
INSERT INTO `chapitre` (`id_chapitre`, `id_lesson`, `nom_chapitre`, `HTML`) VALUES
(143, 10, 'Cloud Cost Pricing', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"what-are-paid-cloud-services-\">What are Paid Cloud Services?</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2ed2IbwBomc?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 04 What Are Paid Cloud Services-\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<p>An accurate cost estimation that meets and exceeds your organization’s budgetary goals requires you to ask important questions, interpret data, and implement AWS best practices</p>\n<h4 id=\"paid-aws-cloud-services-include-\">Paid AWS Cloud Services include:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Running Compute Resources  </li>\n<li>Storage  </li>\n<li>Provisioned Databases  </li>\n<li>Data Transfer    </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Remember, you only pay for services you use, and once you stop using them, AWS stops charging you immediately and doesn’t levy any termination fees.</p>\n<h4 id=\"aws-does-not-charge-for-\">AWS does not charge for:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong> AWS Elastic Beanstalk</strong> - Rapid application deployment  </li>\n<li><strong> AWS Cloud Formation</strong> - AWS Branded Infrastructure as Code service  </li>\n<li><strong> Auto-Scaling</strong> - Scaling EC2 instances up/down or in/out based on your application   requirements  </li>\n<li><strong> AWS IAM</strong> - User and access management  </li>\n</ul>\n<p>There is no cost for uploading data into the AWS cloud, although you will pay for storage and data transfer back out. Because of the massive scale of the AWS technology platform, there is no limit to how much data you can upload. </p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"AWS Costs Include Maintenance, updating and securing\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8be225_cand-c2-l1-costs/cand-c2-l1-costs.jpg\" width=\"943px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Costs Include Maintenance</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"good-cost-hygiene-practices\">Good Cost Hygiene Practices</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Establish a naming convention for Servers and Databases</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Use Tags to track costs by:  </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Group</li>\n<li>Lifecycle</li>\n<li>Person</li>\n<li>Application</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><p>Create IT Governance rules</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Set Billing Alarms</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"costs-in-regions\">Costs In Regions</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NW7RuTsBQFo?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 05 Costs In Regions\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>AWS costs depend on the region\n<br/><br/></li>\n<li>Costs vary due to:   <ul>\n<li>local regulations  </li>\n<li>cost of doing business</li>\n<li>competition</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Least costly region is US East 1 in N. Virginia  </li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"tips-for-reducing-costs\">Tips for Reducing Costs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Use AWS CloudFront to cache data close to end users</li>\n<li>Avoid inter-region data transfer costs</li>\n<li>Peering via AWS Transit Gateway for VPCs reduces costs</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"US East 1 (N. Virginia) is the least costly region and has the most complete suite of services\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8be2a8_cand-c2-l1-us-east-1/cand-c2-l1-us-east-1.jpg\" width=\"653px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>US East 1 (N. Virginia)</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"new-terms\">New Terms</h2>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:left\">Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>11 9’s guarantee</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">99.999999999% durability of objects over a given year. This durability level corresponds to an average annual expected loss of 0.000000001% of objects</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Availability Zones</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">A logical data center in an AWS region with redundant and separate power, networking and connectivity reducing the likelihood of two zones failing simultaneously</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS CloudFront</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Fast content delivery network (CDN) service that securely delivers data, videos, applications, and APIs to customers globally with low latency</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Local Zones</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">A type of AWS infrastructure deployment that places AWS compute, storage, database, and other select services closer to large population, industry, and IT centers where no AWS Region exists today</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Regions</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">A geographical location with a collection of availability zones physically isolated from and independent of every other region</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Support</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Paid support plans offering AWS customers access to AWS technical experts and professional guidance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Durability</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">The probability that the object will remain intact and accessible after a period of one year</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Edge Location</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">A physical site that CloudFront uses to cache copies of your content for faster delivery to users at any location</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fault Tolerance</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">The property that enables a system to continue operating properly in the event of the failure of (or one or more faults within) some of its components</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>High Availability</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Refers to systems that are durable and likely to operate continuously without failure for a long time</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Memory-Optimized</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">The R3 instance class recommended for applications that require high memory performance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Points of Presence</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">AWS Edge Locations and Regional Edge Caches used for both AWS CloudFront and Lambda@Edge to deliver content to end users at high speeds</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Storage-Optimized</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Instances are designed for workloads that require high, sequential read and write access to very large data sets on local storage. They are optimized to deliver tens of thousands of low-latency, random I/O operations per second (IOPS) to applications</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>VPC Peering</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">A networking connection between two AWS VPCs that allows you to route traffic between them using private IP addresses</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>VPC Sharing</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">allows you to share subnets with other AWS accounts in your organization </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(144, 10, 'Exercise: Pricing by Region', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"calculate-infrastructure-cost-in-six-regions\">Calculate Infrastructure Cost in Six Regions</h2>\n<p>AWS prices services differently in each region. This exercise illustrates how region affects the pricing of various services. We will use the <a href=\"https://calculator.aws/#/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Pricing Calculator</a> to estimate the monthly cost of the exact same services in six regions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>N. Virginia</li>\n<li>N. California</li>\n<li>Oregon</li>\n<li>Paris</li>\n<li>Ireland</li>\n<li>Mumbai</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Price out this group of services: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>EC2 <ul>\n<li>8 instances</li>\n<li>Linux operating system </li>\n<li>c5.xlarge </li>\n<li>On-Demand Instances</li>\n<li>General purpose SSD</li>\n<li>30 GB storage</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Elastic Load Balancing<ul>\n<li>1 Application Load balancer  </li>\n<li>Average New Connections per ALB: 10</li>\n<li>Average Number of Requests per second per ALB: 10 </li>\n<li>Average Connection Duration:  1 second</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>S3 Storage<ul>\n<li>4TB </li>\n<li>No data transfer</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Database<ul>\n<li>1 Amazon Aurora Serverless (MySQL Compatible)</li>\n<li>4GB RAM (2 Aurora Capacity Units per hour)</li>\n<li>100GB  Database Storage</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Make a note of the estimates and rank the regions below from lowest to highest cost.  You can use this  to record your results.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ucYYHYN3M8p36MUYT5hmpTRom5-p5ICIPlOqOydARl8/copy\" target=\"_blank\">Google Docs: Costs by Region Worksheet</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/September/5f63d976_costs-by-region-worksheet/costs-by-region-worksheet.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Downloadable: Costs by Region Worksheet</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(145, 10, 'Solution: Pricing by Region', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"my-solution-using-the-aws-pricing-calculator\">My Solution Using the AWS Pricing Calculator</h2>\n<p>Here is how I completed this exercise: </p>\n<h3 id=\"for-ec2\">For EC2</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Select <strong>Create Estimate</strong>, search for and select <strong>Amazon EC2</strong>, then select <strong>Configure</strong>.</li>\n<li>Select the  desired AWS Region from the <strong>Region</strong> dropdown.</li>\n<li>Select <strong>Quick Estimate</strong> and <strong>Linux Operating System</strong></li>\n<li>Choose <strong>Search instances by name</strong> and search for <strong>c5.xlarge</strong>.   </li>\n<li>Add 8 instances to the estimate.  </li>\n<li>Under <strong>Pricing strategy</strong>, select <strong>On-Demand Instances</strong></li>\n<li>Leave the defaults under <strong>Elastic Block Storage</strong>.</li>\n<li>At the bottom of the page, click <strong>Add to my estimate</strong>, and on the next page, select <strong>Add service</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"for-application-load-balancer\">For Application Load Balancer</h3>\n<ol start=\"9\">\n<li>Search for and select <strong>Elastic Load Balancing</strong>, then select <strong>Configure</strong></li>\n<li>Choose one <strong>Application Load Balancer</strong>.  </li>\n<li>Under <strong>Average connection duration</strong>, type 1.  </li>\n<li>Under <strong>Average number of requests per second per ALB</strong>, type 10.  </li>\n<li>Select <strong>Add to my estimate</strong>, then select <strong>Add service</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"for-s3\">For S3</h3>\n<ol start=\"14\">\n<li>Search <strong>S3</strong> (Amazon Simple Storage Service), then select <strong>Configure</strong>.</li>\n<li>Toggle <strong>S3 Standard</strong> <em>ON</em> , and the remaining options <em>OFF</em>.\n16  Under <strong>S3 Standard storage</strong> type 4 , then select TB from the dropdown.</li>\n<li>Select <strong>Add to my estimate</strong>, then select <strong>Add service</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"for-aws-rds\">For AWS RDS</h3>\n<ol start=\"18\">\n<li>Search <strong>RDS</strong> to find <strong>Amazon Aurora (MySQL Compatible)</strong>, then select <strong>Configure</strong>.  </li>\n<li>Select <strong>Aurora Serverless (MySQL Compatible)</strong>. </li>\n<li>Add 2 <strong>Aurora Capacity Units  per hour</strong> and 100GB of <strong>Database Storage</strong>. </li>\n<li>Select <strong>Add to my estimate</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"AWS Pricing Calculator Example\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/May/5eab9335_cand-c2-aws-pricing-us-east-1/cand-c2-aws-pricing-us-east-1.png\" width=\"887px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Pricing Calculator Estimate for US East 1 (N. Virginia)</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>I repeated the process for each of the locations on the list and then I ranked them.</p>\n<p><strong>NOTE</strong>:  Pricing estimates may fluctuate throughout the lifespan of this course because AWS pricing has been shown to decrease over time</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"My Solution to the Costs in the Cloud exercise\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/May/5eab9320_cand-c2-updated-costs-by-region-/cand-c2-updated-costs-by-region-.png\" width=\"746px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>My Ranking of Costs by Region</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<p>As we can see in this exercise, costs vary by region.  And even if the region is in the USA, it doesn’t mean it is less expensive. N California is more expensive than Northern Virginia and Mumbai.</p>\n<p>There are many reasons for the price difference. Supply and demand, local government regulations and taxes, the cost of doing business such as land, construction and electricity.</p>\n<p>Application performance and user satisfaction are the goals of a cloud architect. You will need to decide where to host your application, balancing costs with your performance goals. In some cases you will need to host your application in multiple regions in order to meet your obligations to your users. A strong understanding of how region affects cost will be useful as you advance in your careers.</p>\n<h3 id=\"learn-more-about-cloud-costs-and-pricing\">Learn More About Cloud Costs and Pricing</h3>\n<p>The links below take you to cloud provider documentation on pricing and cost strategies. You will also learn more information about how VPC peering and the AWS CloudFront CDN work. Please follow the links to gain a greater understanding of these technologies when you can.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/pricing/services/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Cloud Services Pricing</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cloud.withgoogle.com/build/infrastructure/public-cloud-pricing-explained/\" target=\"_blank\">Public Cloud Pricing, Explained</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/synaptic-tech/daily-aws-billing-alert-4ea541475ff8\" target=\"_blank\">Daily AWS  Billing Alert</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/peering/what-is-vpc-peering.html\" target=\"_blank\">VPC Peering</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/cloudfront/\" target=\"_blank\">CloudFront Content Delivery Network</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(146, 10, 'Instance Pricing', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"pricing-for-ec2-instances-in-aws\">Pricing for EC2 Instances in AWS</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/px2Iko_Ezao?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 07 Instance Pricing\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<p>AWS EC2 instance pricing is straightforward, but it can quickly become complex when you take up the task of optimizing your environment to achieve the ideal cost/performance balance. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Explore OS licensing pricing and options</li>\n<li>Limit the users and roles that can launch production instances  </li>\n<li>Choose the best instance for your workload  </li>\n<li>Save by moving to new generation instances when available</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"purchasing-options\">Purchasing Options</h3>\n<p>When optimizing your computing usage to reduce your monthly spend, one of the first places you want to count your costs is in your EC2 instances, and one of the best resources here is using reserved instances. </p>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Option                              </th>\n<th>How it Works</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Capacity Reservations</td>\n<td>Reserve capacity for your EC2 instances in a specific Availability Zone for any duration.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dedicated Hosts</td>\n<td>Pay for a physical host that is fully dedicated to running your instances, and bring your existing per-socket, per-core, or per-VM software licenses to reduce costs.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dedicated Instances</td>\n<td>Pay, by the hour, for instances that run on single-tenant hardware.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>On-Demand Instances</td>\n<td>An AWS service or technology that can be acquired at any time for a predetermined standard cos</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Reserved Instances</td>\n<td>An AWS service or technology that can be reserved for a period of time at a discount in exchange for a payment commitment</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Savings Plans</td>\n<td>Reduces your Amazon EC2 costs by making a commitment to a consistent amount of usage, in USD per hour, for a term of 1 or 3 years.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Scheduled Instances</td>\n<td>Purchase instances that are always available on the specified recurring schedule, for a one-year term.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Spot Instances</td>\n<td>an EC2 instance that can be acquired by bidding for a low price in exchange for the understanding that AWS can reclaim it at any time</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"AWS Current Generation Instance Types\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8be92b_cand-c2-l1-instance-types/cand-c2-l1-instance-types.jpg\" width=\"854px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS EC2 Primary Instance Types</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 3</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>How are EC2 Instance Costs Calculated?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By Instance Size</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-10\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-10\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-10\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-10\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By Time of Day</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By Operating System</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By Region</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk5-11\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk5-11\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk5-11\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk5-11\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By Tag</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By Memory/RAM</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk7-12\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk7-12\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk7-12\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk7-12\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>By Corporation</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"reserved-and-spot-instances\">Reserved and Spot Instances</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rlQjQ9XKs2o?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 08 Reserved And Spot Instances Detailed Discussion\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Reserved instances offer a savings of almost 70% in some cases. In exchange for an upfront commitment of 1 or 3  years, AWS offers significant savings, which increases a bit depending on how you choose to pay. Paying in advance will save you even more. </p>\n<p>Spot instances can potentially save customers 90% of AWS on-demand EC2 instance pricing, but there are some significant drawbacks. AWS can terminate a spot instance that is running below the current spot call price at any time after providing you with a  2-minute warning. </p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Reserved instances are a 1 or 3 year commitment and  multiple payment options also save money, </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Spot instances  can be terminated by AWS at any time  with a 2 minute notification  that you might not see</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>On demand instances are the most expensive option and should only be used in short-term or urgent situations.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 3</h3><div class=\"index-module--markdown--2MdcR ureact-markdown\"><p>Match the Instance Model to its Cost Discount Description</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-choices--2ziSF\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Answer choice selections - tab through answer choices to match to concepts below.\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><h3>Submit to check your answer choices!</h3></div></div><div class=\"index--labels--tWrVZ\"><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Cost Discount</p>\n</div></h3><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Model</p>\n</div></h3></div><div class=\"index--answer-selections--3mNdz\"><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Full List Pricing</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Full List Pricing - currently On Demand Instances\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, On Demand Instances.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>On Demand Instances</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Decide and Pay Upfront</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Decide and Pay Upfront - currently Standard Reserved Instances\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, Standard Reserved Instances.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Standard Reserved Instances</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Pay upfront with the option to resize later</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Pay upfront with the option to resize later - currently Convertible Reserved Instances\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, Convertible Reserved Instances.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Convertible Reserved Instances</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Discount in exchange for guaranteed </p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Discount in exchange for guaranteed  - currently Spot Instances\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, Spot Instances.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Spot Instances</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--buttons--2-6jY _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--container--mpad_\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--reflect-header--38-vS\"><h2>Think Like a Cloud Architect</h2></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>How would you architect this EC2 scenario with a combination of On Demand. Reserved, and Spot instances for maximum cost effectiveness?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Running an application on an instance that needs to capture metrics for 7 days straight</li>\n<li>A batch process that runs for 3 hours every night</li>\n<li>A website that has been selling inflatable kayaks for 15 years</li>\n</ul>\n</div><span><div><textarea class=\"open-response-atom--textarea--2YCpW\" placeholder=\"Enter your response here, there\'s no right or wrong answer\"></textarea><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" disabled=\"\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></span></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"new-terms\">New Terms</h3>\n<div class=\"index-module--table-responsive--1zG6k\"><table class=\"index-module--table--8j68C index-module--table-striped--3HHC-\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th>Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>AMI (Amazon Machine Image)</td>\n<td>Provides the configuration details needed to launch an EC2 instance</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"additional-reading-on-instance-pricing\">Additional Reading on Instance Pricing</h3>\n<p>These links provide additional information on EC2 instance types, how they are priced, and how you can use different instances to optimize for cost. Please follow these links to learn more about AWS EC2 instance costs when you reach the end of this lesson.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/regions_az/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Regions</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/instance-types/\" target=\"_blank\">EC2 Instance types</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/new-ec2-spot-blocks-for-defined-duration-workloads/\" target=\"_blank\">Spot Blocks</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.ec2instances.info/\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon EC2 Instance Comparison</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>');
INSERT INTO `chapitre` (`id_chapitre`, `id_lesson`, `nom_chapitre`, `HTML`) VALUES
(147, 10, 'Storage Pricing', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"what-are-the-costs-associated-with-storage-\">What Are the Costs Associated With Storage?</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/855-ZH2W7C0?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 09 What Are Costs Associated With Storage-\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Storage costs vary considerably depending on usage and requirements. </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Applications require different types of optimized storage depending on their primary function.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"selecting-the-right-storage-for-your-application-\">Selecting the Right Storage for Your Application.</h3>\n<p>Selecting the right storage is the key to both satisfied customers and high-performing databases. In general you should select storage based on the following criteria:</p>\n<h4 id=\"ssd-solid-state-drives\">SSD Solid State Drives</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Use flash memory to deliver superior performance and durability without moving parts  </li>\n<li>More durable, run cooler and use less energy  </li>\n<li>Best for i/o intensive applications and database services and boot volumes</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"hdd-hard-disk-drives\">HDD Hard Disk Drives</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Proven technology</li>\n<li>Typically less expensive than solid state drives for the same amount of storage </li>\n<li>Available with more storage space than SSDs  </li>\n<li>Best for throughput intensive workloads like big data analysis and log processing  </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"AWS Storage Options: EFS, EBS, and S#\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8beac0_cand-c2-l1-storage-types/cand-c2-l1-storage-types.jpg\" width=\"876px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Storage Options</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 3</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Choose the best storage type for a throughput intensive big-data workload</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-10\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-10\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-10\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-10\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Cold HDD</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk2-11\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-11\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-11\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk2-11\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>General Purpose SSD</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Throughput Optimized HDD</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-12\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk4-12\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk4-12\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-12\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Provisioned IOPS SSD</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"radio-quiz-atom--buttons--Y7OWz _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 3</h3><div class=\"index-module--markdown--2MdcR ureact-markdown\"><p>Match the S3 Archive Type with its object retrieval timeframe service level agreement (SLA)</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-choices--2ziSF\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Answer choice selections - tab through answer choices to match to concepts below.\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><h3>Submit to check your answer choices!</h3></div></div><div class=\"index--labels--tWrVZ\"><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Usage</p>\n</div></h3><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Archive Type</p>\n</div></h3></div><div class=\"index--answer-selections--3mNdz\"><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>1 minute - 12 Hour SLA</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"1 minute - 12 Hour SLA - currently S3 Glacier\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, S3 Glacier.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>S3 Glacier</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Immediate Retrieval</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Immediate Retrieval - currently S3 IA\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, S3 IA.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>S3 IA</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Within 12 hour retrieval SLA</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Within 12 hour retrieval SLA - currently S3 Glacier Deep Archive \" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, S3 Glacier Deep Archive .\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>S3 Glacier Deep Archive </p>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--buttons--2-6jY _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 3 of 3</h3><div class=\"index-module--markdown--2MdcR ureact-markdown\"><p>Match the feature with the storage service</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-choices--2ziSF\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Answer choice selections - tab through answer choices to match to concepts below.\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><h3>Submit to check your answer choices!</h3></div></div><div class=\"index--labels--tWrVZ\"><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Storage Service Features</p>\n</div></h3><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Storage Service</p>\n</div></h3></div><div class=\"index--answer-selections--3mNdz\"><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Scalable, elastic, and encrypted file storage system that can be used concurrently in the AWS cloud and on-premises</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Scalable, elastic, and encrypted file storage system that can be used concurrently in the AWS cloud and on-premises - currently AWS EFS\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS EFS.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS EFS</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Active Linux-based file system that is procured in advance and best for persistent data</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Active Linux-based file system that is procured in advance and best for persistent data - currently AWS EBS\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS EBS.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS EBS</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Extremely low-cost S3 storage for backup and archiving</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Extremely low-cost S3 storage for backup and archiving - currently AWS Glacier\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS Glacier.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Glacier</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>A high-speed data storage layer that stores a subset of frequently requested data close to the end user so that future requests for that data are served up faster</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"A high-speed data storage layer that stores a subset of frequently requested data close to the end user so that future requests for that data are served up faster - currently Edge Cache\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, Edge Cache.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Edge Cache</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--buttons--2-6jY _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"new-terms\">New Terms</h3>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th>Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Edge Cache</td>\n<td>A high-speed data storage layer which stores a subset of data, typically transient in nature, close to the end user so that future requests for that data are served up faster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>EBS</td>\n<td>Elastic Block Store - cloud-based and pre-allocated linux-based block storage system provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS) that is best used for storing persistent data</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>EFS</td>\n<td>Elastic File System - a simple, scalable, elastic, and encrypted file storage system that can be used by concurrent compute resources in the AWS cloud and on-premises</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>HDD</td>\n<td>Category of EBS hard disk drive. Can be throughput optimized (workhorse) or cold (infrequently scanned)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lifecycle Policies</td>\n<td>Automate the actions you want to take on an object in an S3 bucket over its lifetime,  for example, move them to another storage class, archive them after a number of days or years, or delete them.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>S3</td>\n<td>Amazon Simple Storage Service  is general purpose object storage used for frequently accessed files</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>S3 Endpoints</td>\n<td>A private connection between your VPC and S3 that doesn’t require internet access, potentially reducing NAT gateway costs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>SSD</td>\n<td>Category of EBS solid-state drive. Can be IOPS optimized for databases (fast) or general-purpose for boot volumes and dev/test systems</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Storage Cache</td>\n<td>A high-speed data storage layer that stores a subset of typically transient data</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tagging</td>\n<td>Allows you to name and classify S3 buckets. AWS can provide a usage and cost report based on tags</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"additional-reading-on-storage-pricing\">Additional Reading on Storage Pricing</h3>\n<p>You can learn more about file and object storage in the cloud and how to optimize your storage solution for cost and functionality by following the links provided below. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/nubego/how-to-save-money-with-aws-vpc-endpoints-9bac8ae1319c\" target=\"_blank\">Save Money With AWS VPC Endpoints</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cloudonaut.io/6-new-ways-to-reduce-your-AWS-bill-with-little-effort/\" target=\"_blank\">Reduce Your AWS Bill</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://bluesentryit.com/gain-real-savings-proper-cloud-setup/\" target=\"_blank\">Real Savings Through Proper Cloud Setup</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(148, 10, 'Tagging and Lifecycle Policies', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"tagging-to-track-costs\">Tagging To Track Costs</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/I00g_hIQEeU?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 10 TAGGING Demo\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><blockquote>\n<p><strong>Reminder</strong>:  The AWS user interface changes regularly!!!  </p>\n<p>The UI in the videos may not exactly match what you are seeing in the current version of the AWS Console, but it should give you enough guidance to help you get started.  </p>\n<p>Feel free to explore the AWS Console and try things out -- but <strong>be careful about spinning up expensive resources.</strong> </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>?? <span style=\"color:red; font-weight:bold;\">ALWAYS DELETE ANY RESOURCES YOU CREATE TO AVOID UNNECESSARY CHARGES</span>??</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"tagging-an-s3-bucket-in-aws\">Tagging an S3 Bucket in AWS</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to the S3 console</li>\n<li>Create a bucket </li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Add tag</em></strong></li>\n<li>Enter the <strong><em>Key</em></strong> and <strong><em>Value</em></strong> pairs</li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Create bucket</em></strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Adding Tags to an S3 Bucket in AWS - give each tag a Key and add an optional Value if desired\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61ce0c81_tagging-an-s3-bucket/tagging-an-s3-bucket.png\" width=\"840px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Adding Tags to an S3 Bucket in AWS</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Tags can also be added to an existing bucket by clicking on the bucket in the S3 console, selecting <strong><em>Properties</em></strong> and editing the <strong><em>Tags</em></strong> property.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"best-practices-for-tagging\">Best Practices for Tagging</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Gather input from a variety of cloud stakeholders to determine the best tagging strategy for your organization</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Define your organization’s tags early in the cloud adoption process, and put systems in place to ensure they are being used consistently</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>AWS tags are case sensitive, so you must standardize how your tags are defined to avoid confusion and orphaned data</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>AWS allows you to tag nearly every service that generates costs, so tag everything you can to maintain accurate billing and cost estimates and reports</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"lifecycle-policies\">Lifecycle Policies</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/bgTz2l5U-EQ?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 Lifecycle Slides And Demo\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"s3-lifecycle-policy-configuration\">S3 Lifecycle Policy Configuration</h3>\n<p>S3 Object Lifecycle Policies simplify the task of object lifecycle management. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>A lifecycle configuration is an XML file that defines the actions you want AWS to perform on the object in S3 storage during its lifecycle in AWS. The lifecycle policy is configured in the S3 management console.</li>\n<li>Object lifecycle policies define both transitions and expirations</li>\n<li>Object transitions define when an object is moved to another storage class; for example moving an object from S3 Standard to S3 Standard Infrequently Accessed after 60 days</li>\n<li>Object expirations define when an object needs to expire out of the S3 bucket, and AWS deletes the file when the expiration conditions have been met</li>\n<li>Once an object has transitioned out of S3 standard, it cannot go back. The object would have to be retrieved and re-uploaded to S3 Standard. </li>\n<li>Lifecycle policies automate transitions and expirations to reduce storage costs by moving objects to less costly tiers, archiving them for long term storage, and deleting them to meet governance requirements</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"How a Lifecycle Policy Works\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8becf4_cand-c2-l1-lifecycle-policy/cand-c2-l1-lifecycle-policy.jpg\" width=\"960px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>How a Lifecycle Policy Works</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"adding-a-lifecycle-policy-to-an-aws-s3-bucket\">Adding a Lifecycle Policy to an AWS S3 Bucket</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Click on the bucket in the S3 console</li>\n<li>Select <strong><em>Management</em></strong></li>\n<li>Select <strong><em>Create lifecycle rule</em></strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"In the Management tab for the S3 bucket, select Create lifecycle rule\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61ce0e10_create-lifecycle-rule/create-lifecycle-rule.png\" width=\"1308px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select <strong><em>Create lifecycle rule</em></strong></p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"4\">\n<li>Enter a rule name</li>\n<li>Select the scope, e.g. <em>Apply to all objects in the bucket</em></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Enter a rule name and select the scope\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61ce0f65_name-and-scope/name-and-scope.png\" width=\"851px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Enter a rule name and select the scope</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"6\">\n<li>Select one or more Lifecycle rule actions, e.g. <em>Move current versions of objects between storage classes</em></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Select the desired rule actions\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61ce133e_set-desired-lifecyle-rule-actions/set-desired-lifecyle-rule-actions.png\" width=\"851px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select the desired rule actions</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"7\">\n<li>Define the desired transition for each action</li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Set storage class for transition and days after creation\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61ce1219_choose-transition-settings/choose-transition-settings.png\" width=\"851px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Define settings for transition</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"8\">\n<li>Set expiration dates</li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Set expiration dates for current and non-current versions\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61ce13c2_set-expirations/set-expirations.png\" width=\"851px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Set expiration dates</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"9\">\n<li>Review the actions and expiration dates</li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Create rule</em></strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Review the actions  and click Create rule\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61ce141c_review-actions-and-expirys/review-actions-and-expirys.png\" width=\"851px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Review the actions  and click <strong><em>Create rule</em></strong></p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Quiz Question</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What happens to an object when it transitions to “expired” in a lifecycle policy?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-10\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-10\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-10\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-10\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>It makes a final transition to Glacier Deep Archive</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk2-11\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-11\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-11\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk2-11\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>It transitions to the expiration bucket</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-12\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-12\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-12\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-12\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>It is placed in a deletion review cache</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>It is permanently deleted</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"radio-quiz-atom--buttons--Y7OWz _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"additional-reading-on-tagging-and-lifecycle-policies\">Additional Reading on Tagging and Lifecycle Policies</h3>\n<p>An effective tagging strategy helps you gain visibility into your costs and resource allocation and provide the insights necessary to track your cloud technology goals and direct your company’s cloud initiatives. Please follow the links below to dive deeper into the topic of resource tagging.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/awsaccountbilling/latest/aboutv2//cost-alloc-tags.html\" target=\"_blank\">Using Cost Allocation Tags</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/awscloudtrail/latest/userguide/view-cloudtrail-events-console.html\" target=\"_blank\">Viewing CloudTrail Events</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/answers/account-management/aws-tagging-strategies/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Tagging Strategies</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://d1.awsstatic.com/whitepapers/aws-tagging-best-practices.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Tagging Best Practices</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/user-guide/create-lifecycle.html\" target=\"_blank\">Create Lifecycle Policies</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/object-lifecycle-mgmt.html\" target=\"_blank\">Object Lifecycle Management</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/how-to-set-lifecycle-configuration-intro.html\" target=\"_blank\">Setting Lifecycle Configuration on a Bucket</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/lifecycle-transition-general-considerations.html\" target=\"_blank\">Transitioning Objects Using S3 Lifecycle</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(149, 10, 'Exercise: S3 Lifecycle Policy Configuration', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"s3-lifecycle-policy-configuration\">S3 Lifecycle Policy Configuration</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"task-list-atom--container--WBrU5\"><header class=\"task-list-atom--header--3bRGC\"><h3 class=\"task-list-atom--title--1bHiw\">Create a Lifecycle Policy</h3><h5 class=\"task-list-atom--description--1K-fr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Your company provides media storage for people who are almost famous on the internet. They upload photos and videos daily which receive hundreds of initial views, but not many users view them after a few days. The service you provide is free, and your not-quite famous customers understand you will delete their files in 180 days. </p>\n<p><strong>Design and implement a cost effective lifecycle policy for this scenario.</strong></p>\n</div></h5></header><div class=\"task-list-atom--tasks-container--3MvCe\"><span class=\"task-list-atom--icon-container--3-v6v\">Task List</span><ul class=\"task-list-atom--tasks-checkbox-container--LMF6d\"><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824759--0\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824759--0\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824759--0\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824759--0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Design a Lifecycle policy that includes at least two transitions and an expiration</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824759--1\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824759--1\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824759--1\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824759--1\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Add the Lifecycle Rules to the S3 Bucket</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824759--2\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824759--2\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824759--2\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824759--2\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Review the rules on the Lifecycle page</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li></ul></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(150, 10, 'Solution: S3 Lifecycle Policy Configuration', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"s3-lifecycle-policy-configuration-solution\">S3 Lifecycle Policy Configuration Solution</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/fphqB9PRBBo?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 11 S3 Lifecycle Policy\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><blockquote>\n<p><strong>Reminder</strong>:  The AWS user interface changes regularly!!!  </p>\n<p>The UI in the videos may not exactly match what you are seeing in the current version of the AWS Console, but it should give you enough guidance to help you get started.  </p>\n</blockquote>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"my-solution\">My Solution</h3>\n<p>Your solution might be different, but here is what I came up with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Store the media files in S3 standard for 30 days, then move files to S3 IA  </li>\n<li>Store the media files in S3 IA for 60 days, then move to S3 Glacier and pay AWS for provisioned expedited retrieval if necessary</li>\n<li>Store the media in S3 Glacier for the remainder of the 180 days, then delete per the lifecycle policy  </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>?? <span style=\"color:red; font-weight:bold;\">ALWAYS DELETE ANY RESOURCES YOU CREATE TO AVOID UNNECESSARY CHARGES</span>??</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Quiz Question</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Based on what you learned in the S3 Lifecycle exercise, how many days does an object have to be stored in S3 Standard storage before it can transition to another S3 storage tier?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-13\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-13\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-13\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-13\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>15</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk2-14\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-14\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-14\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk2-14\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>60</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-15\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-15\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-15\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-15\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>1</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>30</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"radio-quiz-atom--buttons--Y7OWz _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>');
INSERT INTO `chapitre` (`id_chapitre`, `id_lesson`, `nom_chapitre`, `HTML`) VALUES
(151, 10, 'DB and Data Transfer Costs', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"aws-managed-databases\">AWS Managed Databases</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/RPXxxY2x0p4?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 12 Discuss AWS Databases, DB Storage, And Licensing-\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points-about-relational-databases\">Key Points About Relational Databases</h3>\n<p>Using AWS RDS provides customers with the advantage of AWS managed services for relational databases You don’t have to worry about managing the hardware supporting the database, patching, or updating.  This  frees you up to innovate in other areas of your stack.</p>\n<h4 id=\"amazon-offers-6-commercially-available-options-for-their-rds-managed-service\">Amazon offers 6 commercially available options for their RDS managed service</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>AWS Aurora  </li>\n<li>MariaDB </li>\n<li>PostgreSQL  </li>\n<li>MySQL  </li>\n<li>Microsoft SQL Server </li>\n<li>Oracle</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"reducing-costs-with-rds-reserved-instances\">Reducing Costs With RDS Reserved Instances</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Based on instance class, database engine and redundancy</li>\n<li>Can bring your own license for Oracle and SQL</li>\n<li>Pay for 1 or 3 year term</li>\n<li>Choose your region thoughtfully -- costs and discounts vary by region </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"relational-sql-vs-non-relational-nosql-databases\">Relational  (SQL)  vs. Non-relational (NoSQL) Databases</h3>\n<p>Relational databases store data in tables. While SQL databases can scale, they are mostly limited to vertical scaling. Costs begin to accelerate as the database scales out.\n<br/><br/>Non-relational databases store data as key-value pairs. NoSQL databases are much more flexible and a good choice when your data structure is likely to change.  They are often used for mobile applications, gaming, and adtech.</p>\n<h4 id=\"aws-dynamodb\">AWS DynamoDB</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Pricing is primarily based on Write Capacity Units (WCUs) and Read Capacity Units (RCUs).</li>\n<li>As with RDS, you also pay for autoscaling, indexing, data transfer, and caching  </li>\n<li>DynamoDB has some additional features and costs that are not associated with RDS databases<ul>\n<li><strong>DAX</strong> - DynamoDB Accelerator (DAX) that uses in-memory caching to reduce latency 10x</li>\n<li><strong>Global Tables</strong> - a multi-region, multi-master database providing fast local read/writes for large global applications by replicating DynamoDB tables across your selected regions</li>\n<li><strong>DynamoDB Streams</strong> - captures and writes streaming records in near real-time for consumption by applications that consume and process streams</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 2</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Which AWS Managed NOSQL database is serverless and delivers millisecond latency?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-13\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-13\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-13\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-13\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Aurora</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS DynamoDB</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-14\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-14\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-14\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-14\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS EBS SSD</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-15\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk4-15\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk4-15\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-15\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS RapidDB</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"radio-quiz-atom--buttons--Y7OWz _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"managing-database-costs\">Managing Database Costs</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/UbyxCyvIcYA?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 13 Procedures And Documentation To Keep Your DB Costs From Becoming Unmanageable\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"best-practices-for-managing-database-costs\">Best Practices for Managing Database Costs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Keep only a subset of the data in RDS</li>\n<li>Move CLOBs and BLOBS to S3 </li>\n<li>Move  historical data to S3.</li>\n<li>Move high velocity frequently written data to DynamoDB</li>\n<li>Do incremental backups  </li>\n<li>Communicate within the same Availability Zone  </li>\n<li>Purchase reserved instances when possible  </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 2</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What are some costs associated with DynamoDB that aren’t associated with AWS RDS? Selects all that apply</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>DAX</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Read Capacity Units</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Global Tables</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk4-16\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk4-16\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk4-16\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk4-16\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Data Transfer</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Streams</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"new-terms\">New Terms</h2>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th>Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Aurora</td>\n<td>fully managed MySQL-compatible relational database engine that combines the speed and availability of commercial databases with the simplicity and cost-effectiveness of open source databases. Aurora is VERY fast-10 times as fast as Microsoft SQL, but slightly more costly</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS DynamoDB</td>\n<td>is a very fast scalable NoSQL database service that manages distri­buted replicas of your data for high availa­bility</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS RDS</td>\n<td>simplifies the process of configuring, operating, and scaling familiar relational databases in the cloud. Provides cost-efficient and resizable capacity for an industry-standard relational database and manages common database administration tasks</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>BLOBS  (Binary Large Objects)</td>\n<td>binary data including videos, images, gifs, and audio files</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>BYOL</td>\n<td>A licensing model that lets companies use their licenses flexibly, whether on-premise, or in the cloud</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>CLOBs (Character Large Objects)</td>\n<td>text data including text files, PDF documents, word processing documents</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>DBA</td>\n<td>A Database Architect is responsible for designing, deploying and managing the data architecture for an organization.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>NoSQL Databases (a.k.a. Non-relational Databases)</td>\n<td>Built for specific data models with flexible schemas for building modern applications and widely recognized for their ease of development, functionality, and performance at scale</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Read Replica</td>\n<td>A read-only copy of a database instance; applications can connect to a read replica just as they would to any DB instance</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"additional-reading-on-database-costs\">Additional Reading on Database Costs</h3>\n<p>The links below will take you to websites with more information about AWS RDS, DynamoDB, database costs, and the difference between SQL and NoSQL databases. Please take time to follow the links and learn more when you can.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/rds/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS RDS</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eMzCI7S1P9M\" target=\"_blank\">Understanding Amazon Relational Database Service</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.sumologic.com/insight/what-is-amazon-rds/\" target=\"_blank\">What is Amazon RDS and What Can It Do?</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/rds/reserved-instances/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS RDS Reserved Instances</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.actifio.com/company/blog/post/using-aws-rds-vs-aws-ec2/\" target=\"_blank\">Using AWS RDS vs. AWS EC2</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/dynamodb/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS DynamoDB</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.thorntech.com/2019/03/sql-vs-nosql/\" target=\"_blank\">SQL vs NOSQL</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(152, 10, 'Hybrid Options', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"manage-costs-with-hybrid-options\">Manage Costs with Hybrid Options</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/SBOeCV033cE?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 14 How Is Hybrid Cloud Implemented\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points-about-hybrid-architecture\">Key Points About Hybrid Architecture</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Helpful when data needs to be in a secure data center due to regulatory and privacy requirements   </li>\n<li>Can be costly, so thoughtful planning is a must!</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"aws-hybrid-cloud-services-aws-outposts-\">AWS Hybrid Cloud Services (AWS Outposts)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Physical compute and storage appliance that resides on-premises in the customer\'s data center</li>\n<li>Provides secure transfer and retrieval </li>\n<li>Encrypts all data at rest and before moving it to the AWS public cloud</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Hybrid Cloud: Cloud + On prem data centers + Edge locations\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8bedc4_cand-c2-l1-hybrid-cloud/cand-c2-l1-hybrid-cloud.jpg\" width=\"843px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Hybrid Cloud</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"implementing-hybrid-cloud\">Implementing Hybrid Cloud</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/hoQMkFTdOdI?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 HybridCloud Slides\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Connecting the on premises data center to the cloud provider requires networking expertise and support from the network team and the cloud technology team</li>\n<li>Connectivity is secured via customer managed gateway and VPN or by AWS Direct Connect</li>\n<li>Data is encrypted end-to-end  </li>\n<li>The VPC provides and manages all of the connections into the cloud environment and resources  </li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"public-vs-private-subnets\">Public vs Private Subnets</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Public subnets</strong> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Have an internet gateway for routes out to the internet from the VPC</li>\n<li>Used for public facing servers like web servers, bastion hosts, proxies, and VPNs</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Private subnets</strong> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>No route to the internet -- but can access the internet using a NAT gateway which is a one-way connection out to the internet   </li>\n<li>Used for backend servers like databases and internal load balancers  </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"AWS VPC - The Brain of the Virtual Network\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8bef2b_cand-c2-l1-vpc/cand-c2-l1-vpc.jpg\" width=\"946px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS VPC - The Brain of the Virtual Network</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"hybrid-cloud-diagram-walkthrough\">Hybrid Cloud Diagram Walkthrough</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget6\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/dbk8TCa5tnI?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=5\" title=\"AWS Hybrid Diagram Walkthru\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"getting-started\">Getting Started</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><p>I\'m using <a href=\"https://www.lucidchart.com/\" target=\"_blank\">LucidChart</a> - but you can use any diagramming tool of your choice for this course.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>In your tool, search for AWS icons. That will make it easier to create an easy-to-follow diagram. </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"hybrid-cloud-diagram\">Hybrid Cloud Diagram</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><p>In this environment, we have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>two public cloud providers (AWS and GCP)</li>\n<li>one corporate data center. </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><p>The cloud environments are connected to the corporate data center through a VPN connection.</p>\n</li>\n<li>The AWS VPN gateway is managed on the AWS side by the AWS Cloud architects and network engineers</li>\n<li>The corporate gateway is managed by the on-premises network engineers. - - The gateways are secured via their local protocols and connected via a secure VPN connection. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>This environment allows the Cloud to share data and resources with the corporate on-premises colo data center.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Hybrid Cloud Architecture example\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8bee82_cand-c2-l1-hybid-cloud-diagram/cand-c2-l1-hybid-cloud-diagram.jpg\" width=\"1650px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Hybrid Cloud Architecture</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Quiz Question</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Which of these are NOT a benefit of using hybrid cloud storage instead on-premise only?</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-13\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-13\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-13\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk1-13\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Data Portability</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Bandwidth Usage</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-14\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-14\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-14\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk3-14\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Data Backup</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-15\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk4-15\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk4-15\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk4-15\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Kick-starts the process of moving to the cloud</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-radio\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk5-16\" class=\"vds-radio__input\" id=\"input--rbk5-16\" name=\"vds-radio\" type=\"radio\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-radio__label\" for=\"input--rbk5-16\" id=\"vds-radio--label--input--rbk5-16\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Fast Storage Procurement</p>\n</div></label></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"radio-quiz-atom--buttons--Y7OWz _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"new-terms\">New Terms</h3>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th>Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Outposts</td>\n<td>A hybrid cloud service that includes a physical AWS compute and storage appliance that resides on -premises in the customer datacenter</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hybrid Cloud</td>\n<td>A mix of public cloud, private cloud on-premise data centers and edge locations</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"additional-reading\">Additional Reading</h3>\n<p>Hybrid cloud expertise is only a click away. Take some time to follow the links below to learn more about cloud storage options, hybrid cloud, and how to integrate the two using cloud services.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.netapp.com/us/info/what-is-hybrid-cloud.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">What is Hybrid Cloud</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/hybrid/\" target=\"_blank\">Hybrid Cloud with AWS</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/products/storage/hybrid-cloud-storage/\" target=\"_blank\">Hybrid Cloud Storage</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/outposts/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Outposts</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/storagegateway/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Storage Gateway</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/datasync/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS DataSync</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/snowball-edge/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Snowball Edge</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://pages.awscloud.com/Introduction-to-Hybrid-Cloud-on-AWS_0315-CMP_OD.html\" target=\"_blank\">Hybrid Cloud on AWS (video)</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h4 id=\"supporting-materials\">Supporting Materials</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8bee9d_cand-c2-l1-hybid-cloud-diagram/cand-c2-l1-hybid-cloud-diagram.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Hybrid Cloud Diagram</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(153, 10, 'Optimizing for Cost', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"intro-to-cost-optimization\">Intro to Cost Optimization</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/L17kXZfryQI?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 16 Optimize Your Environment\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Establish baselines, monitor peak periods and autoscale based on peaks</li>\n<li>Use spot instances strategically to reduce costs</li>\n<li>Private IPs allow you to transfer data for free within the same availability</li>\n<li>Use consolidated billing to save money if your organization has multiple AWS accounts</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"finding-the-cost-performance-sweet-spot\">Finding the Cost/Performance Sweet Spot</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Optimization takes time and skill</li>\n<li>You will probably need to make many small changes</li>\n<li>Don\'t underestimate the role of monitoring  </li>\n</ul>\n<p>With time and experience, it becomes easier to detect areas where optimization is required.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Quiz Question</h3><div class=\"index-module--markdown--2MdcR ureact-markdown\"><p>Match the AWS Service with its function or description</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-choices--2ziSF\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Answer choice selections - tab through answer choices to match to concepts below.\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><h3>Submit to check your answer choices!</h3></div></div><div class=\"index--labels--tWrVZ\"><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Service</p>\n</div></h3><h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Cost Management Tool</p>\n</div></h3></div><div class=\"index--answer-selections--3mNdz\"><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Lets you set custom cost and usage budgets that alert you when those thresholds are exceeded</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Lets you set custom cost and usage budgets that alert you when those thresholds are exceeded - currently AWS Budgets\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS Budgets.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Budgets</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS\'s breadth of services and pricing options that offer the flexibility to effectively manage your costs and still keep the performance and capacity your business requires</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"AWS\'s breadth of services and pricing options that offer the flexibility to effectively manage your costs and still keep the performance and capacity your business requires - currently AWS Cost Optimization\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS Cost Optimization.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Cost Optimization</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Cross-reference your costs and usage to determine which usage types accrue the most cost, and take corrective action</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"Cross-reference your costs and usage to determine which usage types accrue the most cost, and take corrective action - currently AWS Cost Explorer\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS Cost Explorer.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Cost Explorer</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--pair--2zqTz\"><div class=\"index--concept--AV9z3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>The most comprehensive information about your AWS costs and usage</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"index--answer-selection--bwGz3 index--pair-part--1zw9K\"><div aria-dropeffect=\"move\" aria-label=\"The most comprehensive information about your AWS costs and usage - currently AWS Cost and Usage Report\" class=\"drop-zone--drop-zone--38cMu\" role=\"listbox\" tabindex=\"0\"><div aria-label=\"Answer 1, AWS Cost and Usage Report.\" class=\"drag-item--drag-item--3sB2T\" draggable=\"true\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Cost and Usage Report</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"index--buttons--2-6jY _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"additional-reading\">Additional Reading</h3>\n<p>Optimizing costs in the cloud is a skill that takes time, testing and a deep understanding of how costs are calculated. Please follow the links below for additional information to help you hone your cloud cost optimization expertise.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/beN1m9AOsQ0\" target=\"_blank\">Gamifying AWS Cost Optimization</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/aws-cost-management/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Cost Management</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(154, 10, 'Right Sizing From the Start', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"when-to-start-big\">When to Start Big</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/B_-IfsYCL50?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 17 When To Start Big\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<p>It makes sense to “start big” and buy your compute in advance when you know what you need because you have:  </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Predictable Traffic and Workloads  </li>\n<li>A sturdy CI/CD pipeline  </li>\n<li>Strong IT and Dev support</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It makes sense to employ elasticity when you can easily predict your compute needs, for example if your app has:  </p>\n<ul>\n<li>A history of periodic surges  </li>\n<li>The potential for extreme usage</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"aws-services-to-help-manage-your-cloud-budget\">AWS Services to Help Manage Your Cloud Budget</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>AWS Budgets</strong> - allows you to configure custom budgets and alert you when costs exceed the pre-defined or projected cost threshold or are unexpectedly lower than your projected costs.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>AWS Trusted Advisor</strong> - evaluates your AWS environment and provides recommendations for steps you can take to to optimize your AWS environment for cost, performance, security, and redundancy. </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Billing Alarms</strong> - notification that contacts you when your billing threshold is approaching or has been reached  </li>\n<li><strong>AWS CodeGuru</strong> - can evaluate code a it is being written to find the most inefficient, costly, and unproductive lines of code  </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--container--mpad_\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--reflect-header--38-vS\"><h2>Think Like A Cloud Architect</h2><div class=\"open-response-atom--answered-icon--_GQ1N\"></div></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>When does it make sense to start big and when does it make sense to employ elasticity?</p>\n</div><span><div><hr/><div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Your reflection</h3></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-answer-container--2c9-l\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--answer--1QIQc\"><strong class=\"light\">It make sense to start big and employ elasticity when you know you know your infrastructure needs.</strong></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-button-container--8XM8j\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--default vds-button__icon vds-button__icon--left\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\"><i aria-hidden=\"false\" aria-label=\"Edit Answer\" class=\"vds-icon\" role=\"img\"><svg viewbox=\"0 0 32 32\"><path d=\"M15 6a1 1 0 01.117 1.993L15 8h-5a2 2 0 00-1.995 1.85L8 10v12a2 2 0 001.85 1.995L10 24h12a2 2 0 001.995-1.85L24 22v-3l.007-.117a1 1 0 01.876-.876L25 18a1 1 0 01.993.883L26 19v3a4 4 0 01-3.8 3.995L22 26H10a4 4 0 01-3.995-3.8L6 22V10a4 4 0 013.8-3.995L10 6h5zm9.669-.294l.11.102 1.413 1.414a2 2 0 01.102 2.719l-.102.11-1.414 1.413a1.99 1.99 0 01-.896.518 1.98 1.98 0 01-.396.763l-.122.134-7.354 7.354a2 2 0 01-.782.483l-.18.05-1.836.427a2 2 0 01-2.432-2.236l.03-.16.422-1.84a2 2 0 01.41-.829l.125-.138 7.354-7.354a1.99 1.99 0 01.898-.518c.072-.273.204-.535.395-.763l.122-.133 1.414-1.414a2 2 0 012.719-.102zm-4.133 4.344l-7.354 7.354-.422 1.84 1.836-.426 7.354-7.354-1.414-1.414zm2.828-2.828L21.95 8.636l1.414 1.414 1.414-1.414-1.414-1.414z\"></path></svg></i></span></button></div></div></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Things to think about</h3></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Thanks for your response. It makes sense to start with larger instances when you have already captured the metrics required to project your application’s future usage patterns and your application has consistent processing patterns. It also makes sense to start big when you are completely unsure of your applications usage patterns, but it is worth it to you to pay a little more to ensure you don’t experience an application outage due to exhausted resources. This is often the case when the cloud technology team doesn’t have an experienced cloud architect on the team. </p>\n<p>It makes sense to employ elasticity when your application has bursts of activity at predictable intervals. For example, an application that is usually in use from 8-5 will scale up at 7 am and begin to scale down around 6 pm. It will run at reduced compute capacity until the next expected increase in activity and scale up.</p>\n<p>For applications with completely unpredictable usage patterns, it makes sense to size according to the average usage and employ autoscaling so that AWS can respond to an increase/decrease in activity according to the criteria you specify.</p>\n</div></div></span></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>');
INSERT INTO `chapitre` (`id_chapitre`, `id_lesson`, `nom_chapitre`, `HTML`) VALUES
(155, 10, 'Autoscaling', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"autoscaling-in-the-cloud\">Autoscaling in the Cloud</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-FrkfVsPf0g?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 Autoscaling Slides\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Designed to maintain stable performance and control costs</li>\n<li>Scaling can add/remove system resources (<strong>vertical scaling</strong>) or add/remove nodes or workers (<strong>horizontal scaling</strong>)  </li>\n<li>Amazon EC2 Autoscaling uses health notifications and instance status checks to determine the health status of an instance. If an instance is marked unhealthy, it is scheduled for replacement.</li>\n<li>Scaling for all AWS resources is done in the Auto Scaling interface</li>\n<li>Scalable AWS resources include<ul>\n<li>EC2</li>\n<li>EC2 Spot Fleets</li>\n<li>ECS</li>\n<li>DynamoDB</li>\n<li>AWS Aurora</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Vertical Scaling</strong></th>\n<th style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Horizontal Scaling</strong></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Scaling Up and Down</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Scaling Out and In</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Adding more resources to the system (memory and CPU)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Adding more nodes or workers</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Change <strong><em>size</em></strong> of EC2 Instances</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Change <strong><em>number</em></strong> of EC2 Instances</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--container--mpad_\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--reflect-header--38-vS\"><h2>Think Like a Cloud Architect</h2><div class=\"open-response-atom--answered-icon--_GQ1N\"></div></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What is the difference between Scaling Out and Scaling up? Do you believe they accomplish the same objective?</p>\n</div><span><div><hr/><div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Your reflection</h3></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-answer-container--2c9-l\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--answer--1QIQc\"><strong class=\"light\">The difference between Scaling Out &amp; Scaling up:\nScaling Out means to add more nodes or instances (For example adding another EC2 instance)\nbut Scaling Out stands for adding more resources in the same node or instance (modifying memory or storage size...)</strong></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-button-container--8XM8j\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--default vds-button__icon vds-button__icon--left\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\"><i aria-hidden=\"false\" aria-label=\"Edit Answer\" class=\"vds-icon\" role=\"img\"><svg viewbox=\"0 0 32 32\"><path d=\"M15 6a1 1 0 01.117 1.993L15 8h-5a2 2 0 00-1.995 1.85L8 10v12a2 2 0 001.85 1.995L10 24h12a2 2 0 001.995-1.85L24 22v-3l.007-.117a1 1 0 01.876-.876L25 18a1 1 0 01.993.883L26 19v3a4 4 0 01-3.8 3.995L22 26H10a4 4 0 01-3.995-3.8L6 22V10a4 4 0 013.8-3.995L10 6h5zm9.669-.294l.11.102 1.413 1.414a2 2 0 01.102 2.719l-.102.11-1.414 1.413a1.99 1.99 0 01-.896.518 1.98 1.98 0 01-.396.763l-.122.134-7.354 7.354a2 2 0 01-.782.483l-.18.05-1.836.427a2 2 0 01-2.432-2.236l.03-.16.422-1.84a2 2 0 01.41-.829l.125-.138 7.354-7.354a1.99 1.99 0 01.898-.518c.072-.273.204-.535.395-.763l.122-.133 1.414-1.414a2 2 0 012.719-.102zm-4.133 4.344l-7.354 7.354-.422 1.84 1.836-.426 7.354-7.354-1.414-1.414zm2.828-2.828L21.95 8.636l1.414 1.414 1.414-1.414-1.414-1.414z\"></path></svg></i></span></button></div></div></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Things to think about</h3></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Scaling out is the process of adding more resources to spread out a workload. An example would be adding servers to a load  balancer to share a workload. Scaling up is the process of making a resource larger and more powerful in response to an increased workload. An example would be adding RAM or CPUs to a server so it can manage an increase in demand.</p>\n<p>Scaling out is also referred to as horizontal scaling</p>\n<p>Scaling up is also referred to as vertical scaling</p>\n</div></div></span></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"auto-scaling-in-aws-demo\">Auto Scaling in AWS Demo</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZA3InH1RKt4?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 Autoscaling Demo\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><blockquote>\n<p><strong>Reminder</strong>:  The AWS user interface changes regularly!!!  </p>\n<p>The UI in the video and the instructions below may not exactly match what you are seeing in the current version of the AWS Console, but it should give you enough guidance to help you get started.  </p>\n<p>Feel free to explore the AWS Console and try things out -- but <strong>be careful about spinning up expensive resources.</strong> </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>?? <span style=\"color:red; font-weight:bold;\">ALWAYS DELETE ANY RESOURCES YOU CREATE TO AVOID UNNECESSARY CHARGES</span>??</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"how-to-set-up-an-auto-scaling-group-in-aws\">How To Set up an Auto Scaling Group in AWS</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Login to the AWS console at console.amazon.aws.com</li>\n<li>Browse to the EC2 Management page</li>\n<li>Locate and select<strong><em> Auto Scaling Groups</em></strong> in the left menu</li>\n<li><strong><em>Create Auto Scaling group</em></strong> </li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Create a launch template</em></strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\" Create a launch template\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bb9562_click-create-a-launch-template/click-create-a-launch-template.png\" width=\"1413px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p><strong><em> Create a launch template</em></strong></p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"6\">\n<li>Name your template and select an Amazon machine image (AMI)</li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Name your configuration and select an AMI\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bb9e0a_select-ami-image/select-ami-image.png\" width=\"788px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Name your configuration and select an AMI</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"7\">\n<li>Select the <strong><em>Instance type</em></strong> (note that Free tier instances are available)</li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Select the Instance type (t1.micro selected but other options are available)\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bb9f8b_select-instance-type/select-instance-type.png\" width=\"782px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select the Instance type (e.g. t1.micro)</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"8\">\n<li>Select an existing <strong><em>Key pair</em></strong> or create a new one</li>\n<li>Select the default <strong><em>Security group</em></strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Select Key pair (or create a new one)  and select Security group\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bba162_key-pair-and-security-group/key-pair-and-security-group.png\" width=\"788px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select Key pair and Security group</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"10\">\n<li>Click <strong><em>Create launch template</em></strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Click Create launch template\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bba2be_create-launch-template/create-launch-template.png\" width=\"788px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Create launch template</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"11\">\n<li>Click <strong><em>Create Auto Scaling Group</em></strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Click Create Auto Scaling group\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bba38f_click-create-auto-scaling-group/click-create-auto-scaling-group.png\" width=\"788px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Click Create Auto Scaling group</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"12\">\n<li>Name your Auto Scaling group and click <strong><em>Next</em></strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Name your Auto Scaling group and click Next\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bba4b1_name-and-next/name-and-next.png\" width=\"786px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Name your Auto Scaling group and click Next</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"13\">\n<li>Set <strong><em>Availability Zones and subnets</em></strong> and click <strong><em>Next</em></strong> to configure advanced options</li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Set Availability Zones and subnets and click Next or Skip to review \" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bba9d7_save-azs-and-select-review-and-next/save-azs-and-select-review-and-next.png\" width=\"740px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Set Availability Zones and subnets and click Next or Skip to review </p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"14\">\n<li>Click <strong><em>Next</em></strong> again</li>\n<li>Set the <strong><em>Group size</em></strong> and <strong><em>Scaling</em></strong> values</li>\n</ol>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Configure group size and scaling\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2021/December/61bbcf9e_configure-group-size-and-scaling/configure-group-size-and-scaling.png\" width=\"625px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Configure group size and scaling</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><ol start=\"16\">\n<li>Click <strong><em>Next</em></strong> and add <strong><em>Notifications</em></strong> and <strong><em>Tags</em></strong> as desired</li>\n<li>Review your Auto Scaling group and click <strong><em>Create Auto Scaling group</em></strong></li>\n<li>Return to the Auto Scaling menu to view your Auto Scaling Group.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span style=\"color: red; font-weight: bold\">?? Reminder!</span></p>\n<p>If you have set up your Auto Scaling Group for practice, don\'t forget to delete your  Auto Scaling Group and logout of the AWS Console when you are done.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 3</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select the actions that can trigger a scaling event</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>A Lambda Function</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Size of a Queue- long or short</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Time of Day</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Increased or Decreased Demand</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>A prediction</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--container--mpad_\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--reflect-header--38-vS\"><h2>Think Like a Cloud Architect</h2><div class=\"open-response-atom--answered-icon--_GQ1N\"></div></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>One day, when my friend and I were talking about building highly-available, fault-tolerant,  and resilient systems in the cloud, she mentioned that it could be considered a best practice to put all single EC2 instances in an auto-scaling group with a minimum size of 1 and a maximum size of 1. What do you think? What would be the desired outcome of running your single EC2 instances in this type of auto scaling group? Would you consider this configuration to be highly available or fault-tolerant?</p>\n</div><span><div><hr/><div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Your reflection</h3></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-answer-container--2c9-l\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--answer--1QIQc\"><strong class=\"light\">I think that doesn\'t make sense to make sense to configure auto-scaling the range of  [1, 1] for highly available.</strong></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-button-container--8XM8j\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--default vds-button__icon vds-button__icon--left\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\"><i aria-hidden=\"false\" aria-label=\"Edit Answer\" class=\"vds-icon\" role=\"img\"><svg viewbox=\"0 0 32 32\"><path d=\"M15 6a1 1 0 01.117 1.993L15 8h-5a2 2 0 00-1.995 1.85L8 10v12a2 2 0 001.85 1.995L10 24h12a2 2 0 001.995-1.85L24 22v-3l.007-.117a1 1 0 01.876-.876L25 18a1 1 0 01.993.883L26 19v3a4 4 0 01-3.8 3.995L22 26H10a4 4 0 01-3.995-3.8L6 22V10a4 4 0 013.8-3.995L10 6h5zm9.669-.294l.11.102 1.413 1.414a2 2 0 01.102 2.719l-.102.11-1.414 1.413a1.99 1.99 0 01-.896.518 1.98 1.98 0 01-.396.763l-.122.134-7.354 7.354a2 2 0 01-.782.483l-.18.05-1.836.427a2 2 0 01-2.432-2.236l.03-.16.422-1.84a2 2 0 01.41-.829l.125-.138 7.354-7.354a1.99 1.99 0 01.898-.518c.072-.273.204-.535.395-.763l.122-.133 1.414-1.414a2 2 0 012.719-.102zm-4.133 4.344l-7.354 7.354-.422 1.84 1.836-.426 7.354-7.354-1.414-1.414zm2.828-2.828L21.95 8.636l1.414 1.414 1.414-1.414-1.414-1.414z\"></path></svg></i></span></button></div></div></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Things to think about</h3></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Depending on how your company approaches costs vs. availability, you can use an autoscaling group of 1 to make sure that if your EC2 instance experiences problems and can’t perform properly, it will be replaced by the autoscaling group, and your application will experience minimal downtime. Read more about it here <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/healthcheck.html\" target=\"_blank\">Health Checks for Auto Scaling Instances</a> </p>\n</div></div></span></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"new-terms\">New Terms</h2>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th>Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Autoscaling/Auto Scaling</td>\n<td>Automatic changes that add or remove compute resources when certain criteria is met and replacing resources that are not healthy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Horizontal Scaling</td>\n<td>Adding more nodes or workers a.k.a. scaling in and scaling out</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>EC2 Spot Fleet</td>\n<td>A mixed compute model that manages Spot and On-Demand EC2 instances</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vertical Scaling</td>\n<td>Adding more resources to the system (memory and CPU) a.k.a. scaling up and down</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"additional-reading-on-autoscaling\">Additional Reading on Autoscaling</h3>\n<p>To learn more about Auto Scaling and how it can contribute to application stability by automating the AWS response to changes in demand, please follow the links below. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/\" target=\"_blank\">AWS Auto Scaling</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.botmetric.com/blog/aws-auto-scaling-top-11-hard-won-lessons-2/\" target=\"_blank\">Tpo 11 Hard-Won Lessons We’ve Learned about AWS Autoscaling</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/plans/userguide/gs-best-practices.html\" target=\"_blank\">Best Practices for AWS Auto Scaling Plans</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/what-is-amazon-ec2-auto-scaling.html\" target=\"_blank\">What is Amazon EC2 Auto Scaling?</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(156, 10, 'Exercise: Autoscaling', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Autoscaling helps you maintain application availability by scaling your infrastructure as need or demand arises. </p>\n<p>Autoscaling in the cloud often looks like this. An application is performing as expected, when an unscheduled increase in traffic triggers a previously configured autoscaling policy and within 2 minutes, additional EC2 instances have been spun up according to the launch configuration, added to the load balancer, and have joined the servers there previously in processing the work. </p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"task-list-atom--container--WBrU5\"><header class=\"task-list-atom--header--3bRGC\"><h3 class=\"task-list-atom--title--1bHiw\">Autoscaling</h3><h5 class=\"task-list-atom--description--1K-fr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Configure a launch configuration and autoscaling group</p>\n</div></h5></header><div class=\"task-list-atom--tasks-container--3MvCe\"><span class=\"task-list-atom--icon-container--3-v6v\">Task List</span><ul class=\"task-list-atom--tasks-checkbox-container--LMF6d\"><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824517--0\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824517--0\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824517--0\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824517--0\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Create an auto scaling group with at least 2 instances</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824517--1\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824517--1\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824517--1\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824517--1\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Give it a unique name</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li><li class=\"task-list-atom--task-checkbox-item--1387k\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824517--2\" checked=\"\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"10824517--2\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"10824517--2\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--10824517--2\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Autoscale based on CPU</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></li></ul></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(157, 10, 'Solution:  Autoscaling', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"autoscaling-exercise-solution\">Autoscaling Exercise Solution</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/o4TlkS4j894?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 19 Autoscaling Solution\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>:  The AWS user interface changes regularly!!!  </p>\n<p>The UI in the video and the instructions below may not exactly match what you are seeing in the current version of the AWS Console, but it should give you enough guidance to complete the exercise.  </p>\n<p>Feel free to explore the AWS Console and try things out -- but <strong>be careful about spinning up expensive resources.</strong> </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>?? <span style=\"color:red; font-weight:bold;\">ALWAYS DELETE ANY RESOURCES YOU CREATE TO AVOID UNNECESSARY CHARGES</span>??</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"setting-up-an-auto-scaling-group-in-aws\">Setting up an Auto Scaling Group in AWS</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Login to the AWS console at console.amazon.aws.com</li>\n<li>Browse to the EC2 Management page</li>\n<li>Locate and select<strong><em> Auto Scaling Groups</em></strong> in the left menu</li>\n<li><strong><em>Create Auto Scaling group</em></strong> </li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Create a launch template</em></strong></li>\n<li>Name your template and select an Amazon machine image (AMI)</li>\n<li>Select the <strong><em>Instance type</em></strong> (note that Free tier instances are available)</li>\n<li>Select an existing <strong><em>Key pair</em></strong> or create a new one</li>\n<li>Select the default <strong><em>Security group</em></strong></li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Create launch template</em></strong></li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Create Auto Scaling Group</em></strong></li>\n<li>Name your Auto Scaling group and click <strong><em>Next</em></strong></li>\n<li>Set <strong><em>Availability Zones and subnets</em></strong> and click <strong><em>Next</em></strong> to configure advanced options</li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Next</em></strong> again</li>\n<li>Set the <strong><em>Group size</em></strong> and <strong><em>Scaling</em></strong> values</li>\n<li>Click <strong><em>Next</em></strong> and add <strong><em>Notifications</em></strong> and <strong><em>Tags</em></strong> as desired</li>\n<li>Review your Auto Scaling group and click <strong><em>Create Auto Scaling group</em></strong></li>\n<li>Return to the Auto Scaling menu to view your Auto Scaling Group.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span style=\"color: red; font-weight: bold\">?? Reminder!</span></p>\n<p>Don\'t forget to delete your  Auto Scaling Group and logout of the AWS Console when you are done.</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"auto-scaling-considerations\">Auto Scaling Considerations</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Launch configurations are templates used by auto scaling groups to determine what types of EC2 instances to launch</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Launch configurations can be assigned to multiple auto scaling groups, but each auto scaling group can only have one launch configuration</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Autoscaling groups maintain enough instances to meet capacity by performing periodic health checks and terminating and replacing instances that are not healthy.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Autoscaling groups use scaling policies to increase and decrease the number of running instances based on conditions you define, such as memory or CPU limits.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>');
INSERT INTO `chapitre` (`id_chapitre`, `id_lesson`, `nom_chapitre`, `HTML`) VALUES
(158, 10, 'Monitoring and Optimization', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"avoid-cost-surprises-with-monitoring-and-optimization\">Avoid Cost Surprises With Monitoring and Optimization</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/1WmLaYooAlQ?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 20 Monitoring Your Infrastructure With AWS Services\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<p>Monitoring is one of the most important skills to features in AWS, and, without it, costs can run out of control because resources are unlimited. You need a response and support plan. You need appropriate alarms. You need to decide when you are done and when you are in an experimental phase. You need to decide how you are going to share results because monitoring metrics aren’t for everyone to view, particularly if they are tracking individual user activity.</p>\n<h3 id=\"aws-cost-optimization-tools-and-services\">AWS Cost Optimization Tools and Services</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>AWS Cost Explorer</strong> - Enables you to view and analyze your costs and usage in a graph or a report. Cost Explorer is very useful in forecasting costs and predicting where reserved instances may offer cost savings.\n<br/><br/> </li>\n<li><strong>AWS Cost Optimization Monitor</strong> - Analyzes your billing reports and pulls out metrics to make them searchable and displays them in a customizable dashboard for analysis\n<br/><br/> </li>\n<li><strong>AWS Code Guru</strong> -  Helps you proactively improve code quality and application performance with intelligent recommendations. It reviews your code and finds code issues during code reviews before they reach production, including needlessly costly lines of code, race conditions, memory leaks, and runaway logging.\n<br/><br/> </li>\n<li><strong>AWS Solution Architects</strong> - Professional AWS certified engineers who are deployed by AWS to assist customers in solving the most challenging engineering problems. Costs for this assistance vary based on your support agreement and of course, the relative value of your account.\n<br/><br/> </li>\n<li><strong>AWS Account Credits</strong> - Credits are available for startups, non-profits, and academic institutions. It never hurts to ask for AWS credits no matter who you are. </li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"baseline-monitoring\">Baseline Monitoring</h3>\n<p>Maintaining application availability and performance is dependent on a robust and well-defined monitoring policy. Establish your monitoring policy by:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Defining your goals</li>\n<li>Document the resources that require monitoring</li>\n<li>Selecting monitoring tools and tasks</li>\n<li>Deciding who will respond to notifications, alerts, and alarms</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you have created a monitoring policy, you must monitor your resources to establish your <strong>monitoring baseline</strong>. Your baseline is defined as normal resource or service performance in your environment. In order to determine your baseline metrics, you should measure how your environment performs under all anticipated conditions at all times of the day. This will give you an idea of what types of deviations to anticipate, and gives you an opportunity to address them in your monitoring plans. Some typical monitoring metrics for EC2 instances include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>CPU Utilization</li>\n<li>Memory Utilization</li>\n<li>Network Utilization</li>\n<li>Disk Performance and Read/Writes</li>\n<li>Disk Space</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"aws-cloudwatch-monitoring\">AWS CloudWatch Monitoring</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/59Octa-ozAg?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"Cloud Monitoring Demo\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><blockquote>\n<p><strong>Reminder</strong>:  The AWS user interface changes regularly!!!  </p>\n<p>The UI in the videos may not exactly match what you are seeing in the current version of the AWS Console, but it should give you enough guidance to help you get started.  </p>\n<p>Feel free to explore the AWS Console and try things out -- but <strong>be careful about spinning up expensive resources.</strong> </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>?? <span style=\"color:red; font-weight:bold;\">ALWAYS DELETE ANY RESOURCES YOU CREATE TO AVOID UNNECESSARY CHARGES</span>??</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>AWS CloudWatch is a service that monitors your AWS resources and application and reports performance metrics in real time  </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>It can track metrics, alarm and notify based on usage, and make changes to the AWS environment based on changes it detects while monitoring  </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>The CloudWatch management page has default dashboards configured that track useful metrics; users can configure additional custom dashboards tailored to the needs of their account  </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>CloudWatch alarms can both notify when a threshold has been reached or breached, as well as take action based on the alarm; for example, it can restart an instance that is not responding or launch additional instances when a server CPU breaches its maximum threshold  </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"aws-cloudtrail\">AWS CloudTrail</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget6\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vBRaRsfBduE?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=5\" title=\"CAND2 CloudTrail\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>AWS CloudTrail is Amazon’s logging service that provides auditing, governance, and compliance visibility into API calls made in the AWS account.  </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>The API call and details are written to a log file and maintained for 90 days </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>CloudTrail captures who or what made the call, what time it happened, the user or process that took the action, and the service or resource that was affected by the action  </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Cloud trail logs keep a running account of API calls and save them in a secure JSON file called an event. The log can be filtered and searched by metadata like date/time, user, or AWS service, but it can’t be modified.  </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>CloudTrail Logs can be configured to be sent to CloudWatch. Publishing CloudTrail logs to CloudWatch provides the ability to create alarms based on CloudTrail log data and look at CloudTrail log data through the CloudWatch dashboards.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 3</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select the options that best represent the metrics you should capture to monitor the baseline for an EC2 Instance</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Network Utilization</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-13\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-13\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-13\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-13\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Logged on Users</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-14\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-14\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-14\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-14\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Clicks per Second</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>CPU Utilization</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Memory Utilization</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 3</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Read more about <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/codeguru/\" target=\"_blank\"> AWS Code Guru</a>.  What services does it perform? <br/> <em>There may be more than one correct answer.</em></p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>It helps you find the most expensive lines of code and code that potentially decreases application performance</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-15\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-15\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-15\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-15\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>It provides users with training when it detects poorly written code</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-16\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-16\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-16\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-16\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>It refactors bad code and pushes the changes to your repo under the name AWSGuru</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Gives you specific recommendations to fix or improve your code.</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--container--mpad_\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--reflect-header--38-vS\"><h2>Think Like a Cloud Architect</h2><div class=\"open-response-atom--answered-icon--_GQ1N\"></div></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What would you do if you received a large bill from AWS for a mistake you made?</p>\n</div><span><div><hr/><div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Your reflection</h3></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-answer-container--2c9-l\"><div class=\"open-response-atom--answer--1QIQc\"><strong class=\"light\">Review Billing reports to diagnostic and view where the is the mistake and enable CloudWatch alarms and CloudTrail logs resolve it to reduce costs for the next month.</strong></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--edit-button-container--8XM8j\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--default vds-button__icon vds-button__icon--left\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\"><i aria-hidden=\"false\" aria-label=\"Edit Answer\" class=\"vds-icon\" role=\"img\"><svg viewbox=\"0 0 32 32\"><path d=\"M15 6a1 1 0 01.117 1.993L15 8h-5a2 2 0 00-1.995 1.85L8 10v12a2 2 0 001.85 1.995L10 24h12a2 2 0 001.995-1.85L24 22v-3l.007-.117a1 1 0 01.876-.876L25 18a1 1 0 01.993.883L26 19v3a4 4 0 01-3.8 3.995L22 26H10a4 4 0 01-3.995-3.8L6 22V10a4 4 0 013.8-3.995L10 6h5zm9.669-.294l.11.102 1.413 1.414a2 2 0 01.102 2.719l-.102.11-1.414 1.413a1.99 1.99 0 01-.896.518 1.98 1.98 0 01-.396.763l-.122.134-7.354 7.354a2 2 0 01-.782.483l-.18.05-1.836.427a2 2 0 01-2.432-2.236l.03-.16.422-1.84a2 2 0 01.41-.829l.125-.138 7.354-7.354a1.99 1.99 0 01.898-.518c.072-.273.204-.535.395-.763l.122-.133 1.414-1.414a2 2 0 012.719-.102zm-4.133 4.344l-7.354 7.354-.422 1.84 1.836-.426 7.354-7.354-1.414-1.414zm2.828-2.828L21.95 8.636l1.414 1.414 1.414-1.414-1.414-1.414z\"></path></svg></i></span></button></div></div></div><div class=\"open-response-atom--info-text-container--2TYfC text--info--1591w\"><h3>Things to think about</h3></div><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>If you receive a large bill from AWS for a configuration mistake- for example, you may have opened a stream from a source that sends too much data to AWS or mistakenly uploaded a very large data set multiple times, you should first find out where you made your mistake so you can correct it as soon as possible. After you are certain you have mitigated your error and no additional unwanted charges are accumulating, reach out to AWS and explain what happened. In many cases, especially during your yearlong free tier testing, they will be understanding and reverse the charges, but there are no guarantees. </p>\n<p>Unfortunately, they are not going to refund charges when you are surprised and disappointed by how much your crypto mining operations cost, versus how much currency you accumulated, so procure your AWS resources wisely.</p>\n<p>Always make sure you configure a billing alarm for your account. Billing alarms prevent shocking surprise bills.</p>\n</div></div></span></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"additional-reading-about-monitoring-and-optimization\">Additional Reading about Monitoring and Optimization</h3>\n<p>Taking the time to understand monitoring while you are early in your cloud architecture career will pay off in the long run. It\'s worth it to invest time into gaining a deep understanding of how cloud metrics relate to costs and performance and be able to translate monitoring insights into actions for your team and your company. Please follow the links below to read more about how monitoring </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/monitoring_ec2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Monitoring Amazon EC2</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/new-ec2-auto-scaling-groups-with-multiple-instance-types-purchase-options/?&amp;trk=ha_a131L000005uJTZQA2&amp;trkCampaign=pac-edm-2019-spot-sitemerch-autoscalingblog&amp;sc_ichannel=ha&amp;sc_icampaign=Adoption_Campaign_pac-edm-2019-spot-site_merch-adoption-all-auto_scaling_console_test&amp;sc_ioutcome=Enterprise_Digital_Marketing\" target=\"_blank\">Launch Autoscaling groups with On Demand, Reserved, and Spot Instances</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/monitoring_automated_manual.html\" target=\"_blank\">Automated and Manual EC2 Monitoring</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uuBuc6OAcVY\" target=\"_blank\">Monitor All Your Things (VIDEO)</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_eWaPVski6o\" target=\"_blank\">Monitoring Performance With CloudWatch Dashboards</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(159, 10, 'Lesson Recap', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"costs-in-the-cloud-recap\">Costs in the Cloud Recap</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jwzUyrradNk?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L1 22 Here Is What You\'Ve Learned\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Costs in the cloud have no equivalent in the data center because cloud services are billed like utilities - you only pay for what you use<br/><br/> </li>\n<li>Costs vary between AWS Regions based on location, regulations, utilities, real estate costs, and the cost of doing business<br/><br/> </li>\n<li>AWS can help architects by providing several calculation and cost optimization services to ensure customers are running cost and performance optimized workloads whenever possible<br/><br/> </li>\n<li>AWS offers significant discounts when you commit to compute and when you need compute for fault-tolerant applications</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Topics we covered in L1\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e8bf3cc_cand-c2-l1-what-learned/cand-c2-l1-what-learned.jpg\" width=\"631px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>What We’ve Learned</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"further-research-on-cloud-costs-and-monitoring\">Further Research on Cloud Costs and Monitoring</h2>\n<p>Managing the costs of your cloud services can be complex, and it requires your expertise and attention. Learning to manage cloud costs is a skill that will lead to successful budgetary goals and savings for your company. When you have time, please follow the links below to learn more about managing costs in the cloud. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://jatheon.com/blog/aws-reduce-costs/\" target=\"_blank\">How to Have Your AWS Budget Under Control</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws-cost-management/beginners-guide-to-aws-cost-management/\" target=\"_blank\">A Beginner’s Guide to AWS Cost Management</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.teampay.co/insights/manage-cloud-costs/\" target=\"_blank\">Manage Cloud Costs</a> </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(160, 10, 'Glossary', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"new-terms-in-this-lesson\">New Terms in This Lesson</h2>\n<p><br/>\n<br/> </p>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Term</th>\n<th>Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>11 9’s guarantee</td>\n<td>99.999999999% durability of objects over a given year. This durability level corresponds to an average annual expected loss of 0.000000001% of objects</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AMI (Amazon Machine Image)</td>\n<td>Provides the configuration details needed to launch an EC2 instance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Autoscaling/ Auto Scaling</td>\n<td>Automatic changes that add or remove compute resources</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Availability Zones</td>\n<td>A logical data center in an AWS region with redundant and separate power, networking and connectivity reducing the likelihood of two zones failing simultaneously</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Aurora</td>\n<td>Fully-managed MySQL-compatible relational database engine that combines the speed and availability of commercial databases with the simplicity and cost-effectiveness of open source databases. Aurora is VERY fast-10 times as fast as Microsoft SQL, but slightly more costly</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS CloudFront</td>\n<td>Fast content delivery network (CDN) service that securely delivers data, videos, applications, and APIs to customers globally with low latency</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS DynamoDB</td>\n<td>Very fast scalable NoSQL database service that manages distri­buted replicas of your data for high availa­bility</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Local Zones</td>\n<td>A type of AWS infrastructure deployment that places AWS compute, storage, database, and other select services closer to large population, industry, and IT centers where no AWS Region exists today</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Outposts</td>\n<td>A hybrid cloud service that includes a physical AWS compute and storage appliance that resides on-premise in the customer datacenter</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS RDS</td>\n<td>Relational database that simplifies the process of configuring, operating, and scaling. Provides cost-efficient and resizable capacity for an industry-standard relational database and manages common database administration tasks</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Regions</td>\n<td>A geographical location with a collection of availability zones physically isolated from and independent of every other region</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AWS Support</td>\n<td>Paid support plans offering AWS customers access to AWS technical experts and professional guidance</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>BLOBS (Binary Large Objects)</td>\n<td>Used to store binary data including videos, images, gifs, and audio files</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>BYOL</td>\n<td>A licensing model that lets companies use their licenses flexibly, whether on-premise, or in the cloud</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Capacity Reservations</td>\n<td>Reserve capacity for your EC2 instances in a specific Availability Zone for any duration.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>CLOBs (Character Large Objects)</td>\n<td>Used to store text data including text files, PDF documents, word processing documents</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>DBA</td>\n<td>A Database Architect is responsible for designing, deploying and managing the data architecture for an organization.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dedicated Hosts</td>\n<td>Pay for a physical host that is fully dedicated to running your instances, and bring your existing per-socket, per-core, or per-VM software licenses to reduce costs.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dedicated Instances</td>\n<td>Pay, by the hour, for instances that run on single-tenant hardware.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Durability</td>\n<td>The probability that the object will remain intact and accessible after a period of one year</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>EBS</td>\n<td>Elastic Block Store - cloud-based block storage system provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS) that is best used for storing persistent data</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>EC2 Spot Fleet</td>\n<td>A collection of EC2 Spot and On-Demand instances</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Edge Cache</td>\n<td>A high-speed data storage layer which stores a subset of data, typically transient in nature, close to the end user so that future requests for that data are served up faster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Edge Location</td>\n<td>A physical site that CloudFront uses to cache copies of your content for faster delivery to users at any location</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>EFS</td>\n<td>Elastic File System - a simple, scalable, elastic, and encrypted file storage system that can be used by concurrent compute resources in the AWS cloud and on-premises</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fault Tolerance</td>\n<td>The property that enables a system to continue operating properly in the event of the failure of (or one or more faults within) some of its components</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>HDD</td>\n<td>Category of EBS hard disk drive. Can be throughput optimized (workhorse) or cold (infrequently scanned)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>High Availability</td>\n<td>Refers to systems that are durable and likely to operate continuously without failure for a long time</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Horizontal Scaling</td>\n<td>Adding more nodes or workers a.k.a. scaling in and scaling out</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hybrid Cloud</td>\n<td>A mix of public cloud, private cloud on-premise data centers and edge locations</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lifecycle Policies</td>\n<td>Automate the actions you want to take on an object in an S3 bucket over its lifetime,  for example, move them to another storage class, archive them after a number of days or years, or delete them.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Memory-Optimized</td>\n<td>The R3 instance class recommended for applications that require high memory performance</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>NoSQL Databases</td>\n<td>Built for specific data models with flexible schemas for building modern applications and widely recognized for their ease of development, functionality, and performance at scale</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>On-Demand Instances</td>\n<td>An AWS service or technology that can be acquired at any time for a predetermined standard cos</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Points of Presence</td>\n<td>AWS Edge Locations and Regional Edge Caches used for both AWS CloudFront and Lambda@Edge to deliver content to end users at high speeds</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Read Replica</td>\n<td>A read-only copy of a database instance; applications can connect to a read replica just as they would to any DB instance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Reserved Instances</td>\n<td>An AWS service or technology that can be reserved for a period of time iat a discount in exchange for a payment commitment</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>S3</td>\n<td>Amazon Simple Storage Service general purpose storage used for frequently accessed files</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>S3 Endpoints</td>\n<td>A private connection between your VPC and S3 that doesn’t require internet access, potentially reducing NAT gateway costs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Savings Plans</td>\n<td>Reduces your Amazon EC2 costs by making a commitment to a consistent amount of usage, in USD per hour, for a term of 1 or 3 years.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Scheduled Instances</td>\n<td>Purchase instances that are always available on the specified recurring schedule, for a one-year term.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>SDD</td>\n<td>Category of EBS solid state drive. Can be IOPS optimized for databases (fast) or general purpose for boot volumes and dev/test systems</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Spot Instances</td>\n<td>an EC2 instance that can be acquired by bidding for a low price in exchange for the understanding that AWS can reclaim it at any time</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Storage Cache</td>\n<td>A high-speed data storage layer that stores a subset of typically transient data</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Storage-Optimized</td>\n<td>Instances are designed for workloads that require high, sequential read and write access to very large data sets on local storage. They are optimized to deliver tens of thousands of low-latency, random I/O operations per second (IOPS) to applications</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tagging</td>\n<td>Allows you to name and classify S3 buckets. AWS can provide a usage and cost report based on tags</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vertical Scaling</td>\n<td>Adding more resources to the system (memory and CPU) a.k.a. scaling up and down</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>VPC Peering</td>\n<td>A networking connection between two AWS VPCs that allows you to route traffic between them using private IP addresses</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>VPC Sharing</td>\n<td>allows you to share subnets with other AWS accounts in your organization</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(161, 11, 'Performance in the Cloud', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ENcEbRD_37g?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L2 01 Intro To Performance And Scalability\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"key-points\">Key Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Moving your applications to the cloud doesn’t guarantee that your performance issues will automatically be resolved, especially if you lift and shift.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>AWS provides services that will assist you in improving your application performance, but optimization is the key. </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In this lesson we\'ll explore the following topics related to performance in the cloud:   </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Scaling  </li>\n<li>Storage  </li>\n<li>Archive  </li>\n<li>Database  </li>\n<li>Message Queues  </li>\n<li>Networking  </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Optimizing Cloud Performance\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e9132c0_cand-c2-l2-performance/cand-c2-l2-performance.jpg\" width=\"524px\"/></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>');
INSERT INTO `chapitre` (`id_chapitre`, `id_lesson`, `nom_chapitre`, `HTML`) VALUES
(162, 11, 'Performing & Underperforming', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"infrastructure-performance-in-the-cloud\">Infrastructure Performance in the Cloud</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/upgjjKN3G8g?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L2 02 Infrastructure Performance In The Cloud\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"optimization-game-plan\">Optimization Game Plan</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Run performance tests</li>\n<li>Capture and analyze metrics</li>\n<li>Select the optimal instance  </li>\n<li>Monitor for outliers to make sure the optimal instance continues to be optimal</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"best-practices-for-optimizing-for-performance\">Best Practices for Optimizing for Performance</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Design your workload infrastructure with performance in mind from the start</li>\n<li>Whenever possible, design your workload or application to be cloud native</li>\n<li>Utilize compute elasticity to manage performance peaks and valleys </li>\n<li>Optimize until your performance meets benchmarks</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"have-the-optimized-instances-changed-\">Have the Optimized Instances Changed?</h4>\n<p>AWS is constantly changing. Check to see the latest optimized instance types here: <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/instance-types/\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon EC2 Instance Types</a></p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"AWS Optimized instance families February 2020\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e913383_cand-c2-l2-instance-types/cand-c2-l2-instance-types.jpg\" width=\"931px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Optimized instance families February 2020</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 2</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select the EC2 Instance Family Optimization Options available in AWS</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Memory</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-13\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk2-13\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk2-13\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk2-13\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Page Load</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>GPU</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Burstable</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk5-14\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk5-14\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk5-14\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk5-14\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Monitoring</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"how-do-you-know-when-your-app-isn-t-performing-\">How Do You Know When Your App Isn\'t Performing?</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget4\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/SypqxdP5zMs?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=3\" title=\"ND063 C2 L2 03 How Do You Know Your App Isn\'T Performing-\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"questions-to-ask-when-you-have-a-performance-issue\">Questions to Ask When You Have A Performance Issue</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>How did this workload get into our environment?</li>\n<li>Did you lift and shift or did you design the application to be cloud native from the start?</li>\n<li>Did you accidentally over-optimize your compute and not leave any room for unexpected performance peaks or periods of high activity?</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"what-aws-services-can-do-when-problems-are-detected\">What AWS Services Can Do When Problems Are Detected</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Spin up instances (scale out)</li>\n<li>Terminate instances</li>\n<li>Increase memory</li>\n<li>Optimize network routes  </li>\n<li>Failover to a backup  </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Even though your application or workload may not be cloud native, you still have an incredible variety of options for improving your performance and avoiding outages and incidents</p>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 2 of 2</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Select the Performance factors affecting workloads in the cloud that you probably cannot control</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk1-15\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk1-15\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk1-15\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk1-15\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Slow Database reads</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Mobile network unreachable</p>\n</div></div></div></li><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-checkbox\"><input aria-labelledby=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-16\" class=\"vds-checkbox__input\" id=\"input--rbk3-16\" name=\"vds-checkbox\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"\"/><label class=\"vds-checkbox__label\" for=\"input--rbk3-16\" id=\"vds-checkbox--label--input--rbk3-16\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Page not found errors</p>\n</div></label><i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"vds-icon vds-icon--sm\" role=\"img\"><svg height=\"24\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"24\"><path d=\"M17 5.3a1.2 1.2 0 1 1 2 1.4l-7.8 12c-.4.6-1.3.7-1.9.2l-4.2-4.2A1.3 1.3 0 0 1 7 12.9l3 3.1 7-10.7z\"></path></svg></i></div></div></li><li class=\"answer-correct--3Mf9Q answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"answered-label--2HFP8\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>AWS Service outage</p>\n</div></div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"checkbox-quiz-atom--buttons--cp1vx _quiz-atom--buttons--3vJgG\"><button class=\"vds-button vds-button--primary\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"vds-button__content\">Submit</span></button></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"new-terms\">New Terms</h3>\n<div class=\"_3iP2TrDXtmCaMBMDFgM-Os\"><table class=\"_31OI8Tmq3yywD_20_EuBtM _1pZkqGvd1RdMO5JXUl_2oA\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"text-align:left\">Term</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:left\">Definition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Burstable Performance Instances</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">T3, T3a, and T2 instances, are designed to provide a baseline level of CPU performance with the ability to burst to a higher level when required by your workload</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Elasticity</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">The ability to grow or shrink infrastructure resources dynamically as needed to automatically adapt to workload changes, maximizing the use of resources and resulting in savings in infrastructure costs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">GPU  (Graphics Processing Unit)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">A programmable chip used to manage and boost the performance of video and graphics. GPU renders images, animations, and video for the computer\'s screen</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Instance Family</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Six distinct classifications of EC2 instance optimized for different types of applications</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Lift and  Shift</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">The process of moving your application from an on-premises environment to the cloud without making any major changes to the code</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Optimized Instances</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Instance types optimized to fit different use cases. Instance types comprise varying combinations of CPU, memory, storage, GPU, and networking capacity and give you the flexibility to choose the appropriate mix of resources for your applications</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Workload</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">A collection of resources and code that delivers business value, such as a customer-facing application or a backend process</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div></span></div>'),
(163, 11, 'Scaling and Performance', '<div class=\"_main--content-container--ILkoI\"><span><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h2 id=\"scaling-elasticity-and-bursting\">Scaling, Elasticity, and Bursting</h2>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"video-atom--video--1rflY\"><div aria-label=\"Loading…\" class=\"vds-loading vds-loading--md\" role=\"status\"><div class=\"vds-loading__children\"><div class=\"_1UN_ejel6QzQCa_M5Nn4bu\"><div class=\"_2lGVVA99VY-snhn6dzPP-z\"><div class=\"_3h3jXAJ1HmC2_sa49itKME _2nvHtsDYiD14gMJ8MpUp2c\"><div class=\"\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"1\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" id=\"widget2\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/qB2-s_eocJI?showinfo=0&amp;rel=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;vq=hd720&amp;hl=en-us&amp;cc_load_policy=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fclassroom.udacity.com&amp;widgetid=1\" title=\"ND063 C2 L2 04 Scaling, Elasticity, And Bursting\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div class=\"ltr\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><h3 id=\"scaling-elasticity-and-bursting\">Scaling, Elasticity, and Bursting</h3>\n<p>The three primary functions built in to AWS to address increases in compute demand are bursting, elasticity and scaling </p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Burstable instances provide your application a baseline level of CPU performance with the ability to burst to a higher level when required by your workload. These instances are great for workloads like fast interactive applications, moderately sized databases, and lower lifecycles like Development and test.. AWS burstable instances are T2 and T3 instance types.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Elasticity is the ability to acquire resources as you need them, and elasticity is ALSO releasing resources when you no longer need them. A service isn’t elastic unless it releases resources it no longer needs, another major cloud differentiator. </p>\n</li>\n<li><p>AWS Auto Scaling monitors your applications based on criteria you specify and automatically adjusts capacity to maintain availability and performance. Autoscaling is an example of scaling up when you add servers as you need them, and scaling down when you wind down and terminating servers you no longer need</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><span></span><div aria-label=\"Show Image Fullscreen\" class=\"image-atom--image-atom--1XDdu\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"image-atom-content--CDPca\"><div class=\"image-and-annotations-container--1U01s\"><img alt=\"Instance Types: Burstable, Elastic and Auto Scaling\" class=\"image--26lOQ\" src=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/April/5e913473_cand-c2-l2-burstable/cand-c2-l2-burstable.jpg\" width=\"947px\"/></div><div class=\"caption--2IK-Y\"><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>Instance Types</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div><span></span></div><span></span></div></div><div><div class=\"index--container--2OwOl\"><div class=\"index--atom--lmAIo layout--content--3Smmq\"><div><div class=\"container--3sWx1\"><div class=\"prompt--1YMnx\"><h3 class=\"question-number--3IlDk\">Question 1 of 3</h3><div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown\"><p>The ability to acquire and release resources a needed is called</p>\n</div></div><ul><li class=\"answer--P2U4D\"><div class=\"status--3geHI\"><div class=\"vds-r